title: salmon casserole
directions: Mix and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt the margarine.
Add the coconut and chopped pecans. Brown lightly and set aside.
Combine the cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk using a mixer.
Fold in the whipped topping.
Put 1/4 of this mixture into each pie shell.
Drizzle 1/4 jar of the caramel sauce on each.
Sprinkle with 1/4 of the coconut mixture on each pie.
Repeat layer.
Freeze well and serve right from the freezer.

title: souper rice
directions: In saucepan combine soup, water, garlic powder, onion powder and rice.
Over medium heat, heat to boiling.
Cover; cook over low heat 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed. Serves 4.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into pies.
Makes about 15 half moon pies.

title: pumpkin nut cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices together.
Stir in dry ingredients and mix until blended.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: garlic twists
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix cheese, oregano and garlic.
Dip biscuits first in butter, then in cheese mixture.
Twist each biscuit and place in a muffin tin.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until filling is firm.

title: southern-style baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni; drain.
To heat macaroni in same saucepan, add remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese; mix well.
Cook and stir over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes until cheese melts.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart shallow dish or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Drain off fat.
Add all ingredients. Bring to boil.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until peas and barley are soft.

title: crabmeat puffs
directions: Let margarine and cheese soften to room temperature.
Mix together with mayonnaise, garlic salt and seasoned salt.
Add flaked crabmeat. Split English muffins in half and spread with crab mixture.

Place them on a pan and put into freezer for 10 minutes. Remove from freezer and place under broiler until bubbly. After being removed from the freezer, the muffins may be cut into small pieces and used as an appetizer.

title: cashew nut salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: pumpkin cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy, gradually adding sugar combined with spices.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Beat in pumpkin and vanilla.
Pour into prepared shell. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
During last 15 minutes of baking, pecan halves may be placed on top as decoration.
Chill before serving.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Heat oven to 325°. In bowl, combine all ingredients except crab and cheese. Gently fold in crabmeat. Turn into 8-inch square ovenproof dish. Sprinkle top with cheese. (At this point, the dish can be covered and refrigerated up to 24 hours before baking.) Bake 30 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with crackers.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix together into casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pecan brownies
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add other ingredients. Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: strufoli(honey clusters)
directions: Mix dough well.
Cut off pieces; roll into strips.
Cut strips into small pieces on slant; place a few at a time in saucepan with hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.
Set aside; drain on paper towels.

title: roast pork
directions: Make 8 slits in meat.
Insert 1/2 clove garlic and 1/2 teaspoon rosemary in each slit.
Shake salt and pepper in each slit.
Dust with salt and pepper.
Put in roasting pan.
Cook at 350° for 2 hours or until done.

title: turnip greens with cornmeal dumplings
directions: Cook turnips until done using plenty of liquid; remove turnips.

title: country garden potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes for 20 to 25 minutes with skins and cut in half. Layer cut side up in 8 x 12-inch pan.
Pour the milk over.
Chop green and red pepper and arrange peppers and chopped onion over the potatoes.
Melt butter and drizzle over top.
Sprinkle salt and pepper to taste.
Top with parsley and then spread grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: stephen's chicken enchilada
directions: Stuff chicken with 1 onion.
Place in pot; cover with water. Add bay leaves and peppercorns; boil until chicken is cooked. Reserve 1 quart chicken broth for Enchilada Sauce.

title: bavarian cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add chopped cabbage.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Serves 4.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix eggs and milk lightly.
Stir in sausage and cheese.
Pour into a 9 x
13-inch casserole dish. Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes, until firm.

title: kitty's best cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Let cool.
Punch holes with fork.
Cook pineapple and sugar together for 15 minutes.
Pour over cake after cooling.
Make pudding as directed on box.
Spread over cake and pineapple.
Add coconut and nuts.
Chill overnight.

title: three layer pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and pat into a 13 x 9 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes and cool completely.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread on crust.
Prepare pudding mixes with 2 c. milk each.
Spread vanilla pudding over cream cheese mixture, then top with chocolate pudding. Refrigerate.

title: white creamy icing
directions: Try a little mirth;

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Stir together sugar and cocoa in iron skillet.
Add egg, cream and salt.
Mix well and cook over medium heat to soft ball stage. Pour into bowl, add vanilla and butter.
Beat until smooth and cool enough to spread on cake.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer except sweet milk. Pour into ice cream cannister and finish filling up with sweet milk.
Stir and then freeze.

title: seafood chowder
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients except white fish. Cook over low heat 10 minutes;
stir now and then.
Add white fish;
cook
minutes
more.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes about 9 1/2 cups.

title: dried apricot-pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, combine pumpkin, sugar, oil and eggs until well blended. In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and spices. Add to pumpkin mixture and blend. Fold in pudding mix. Stir in apricots and nuts. Pour into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch bread pans. Bake 1 hour or until tester inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; remove breads to wire rack. Makes 2 loaves.

title: corn for canning or freezing
directions: Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Put in cans and cook 25 minutes at 10 pounds pressure, or freeze.
Add water if there is not enough liquid to cover corn in cans.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Grind 12 small peppers fine and drain.
Old pillow case does fine.
Pack down to make 2 cups.
Do the same to jalapeno or chili peppers.
Mix all ingredients except Certo in kettle and boil hard for 2 minutes.
Stir in certo and bring back to hard boil.
Pour in jars and seal.
Makes 4 to 5 pints.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans. Place green beans in casserole dish. Salt and pepper to your taste. Add cream of mushroom soup and milk. Stir well. Top with onion rings. Bake at
350° for 30 minutes.

title: chewy granola bars
directions: Mix all.
Press mixture in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; cut.
Healthy!!

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook lasagna noodles as directed.
In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook broccoli and green onions in salad oil until tender (about 5 minutes), stirring frequently.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Stir in cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, salt and egg. Preheat oven to 375°.
Drain noodles and place in single layer on waxed paper.
Evenly spread some cheese mixture on each lasagna noodle.
Roll up each noodle jelly-roll fashion.

title: sweet sour broccoli and cauliflower
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower separately.
Follow package directions if using frozen vegetables.
Or, cook fresh vegetables until tender-crisp.
Drain.
Turn into warm serving dish.
While vegetables cook, put bacon into frying pan and cook until crisp. Remove bacon and reserve.
Pour out all but 3 tablespoons of the bacon drippings.
Add onions.
Saute for 2 minutes, then stir in brown sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Heat.
Pour sauce over cauliflower and broccoli in serving dish.
Top with crisp bacon. Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Fold in nuts and apples.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: grape catsup
directions: Pick over and wash grapes; crush in a large saucepan and cook without water until the juice flows freely.
Press through cheesecloth or sieve to keep back the skins and seeds.
Combine pulp with all remaining ingredients and simmer very slowly until desired consistency.
Put into sterilized jars and seal.
Very good with fish.

title: salmon croquettes(100 portions; each portion:  2 croquettes)
directions: Combine milk and 2 1/2 quarts bread crumbs; mix until there are no lumps.
Add all ingredients, except cracker crumbs; to milk and crumb mixture; mix well.
Cover container with waxed paper; store in refrigerator to chill well before shaping.
Dip chilled mixture with a number 12 scoop; shape into croquettes.
Roll in crumbs. Fry in deep fat (350°) until golden brown.
May be baked as a loaf or in 2-ounce patties and grilled on a 375° griddle without coating.

title: chilled fruit in cream
directions: Mix all canned fruit in a bowl.
Set aside.
Mix both cans of milk with hand mixer for 5 minutes.
Pour milk in with fruit. Stir lightly with spoon and chill.
When iced, take out and stir. Put back in freezer to chill overnight.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: hamburger hash browns
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread hash browns in pan.
Sprinkle salt, then brown hamburger, onions, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle corn and hamburger over potatoes.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Pour over.
Place at least 6 slices of Velveeta or more to cover.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 45 minutes at 350°. Remove foil and spread French fried onions on top.
Turn off oven and heat 15 minutes.

title: fideo
directions: Saute vermicelli in oil until light brown. Drain on paper towels.
Place in casserole. Brown onion and garlic.
Add tomatoes and broth. Add salt, pepper and cumin.
Cover the vermicelli with sauce.
Cover the casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour, adding more broth as liquid is absorbed.

title: magic bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour condensed milk over crumbs.
Sprinkle chips, then coconut and nuts.
Press firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting.
Chill, if desired.

title: syrups
directions: Heat water to boiling point; lower heat and add sugar.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Add maple flavoring or another flavoring for personal taste.

title: crock-pot scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and onions thin.
Put a layer of potatoes, a layer of cheese, a layer of onions until crock-pot is full.
End up with a layer of potatoes on top.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Cook on high setting 1/2 day or on low setting all day.

title: apricot delight salad
directions: Boil pineapple and juice.
Add buttermilk and jello.
Stir well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until set.
Serves 6.

title: party rye parmesan
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Spread on party rye.
Broil until bubbly.

title: caramel pecan nuggets
directions: Melt caramels in milk over low heat, then add pecans when completely melted.
Drop by spoon onto buttered wax paper.
Chill.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients with a fork and press in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together. Beat eggs until light and add.
Press bananas through sieve or just mash and add lemon juice.
Blend with creamed mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and mix quickly into banana mixture.
Add nuts. Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut blossoms with hershey's kisses
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
With a tablespoon scoop out the dough and roll into balls.
Add additional sugar for rolling the balls.
Put the balls on baking sheet one inch apart and bake them at 350°.
When cookies are more than half done add in the center Hershey's Kisses.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix egg, milk and salt.
Add enough flour to make stiff dough. Roll dough on a floured surface.
Dough should be thin.
Let dough rest for 20 minutes.
Starting on longest side, roll dough up loosely; cut into 1/4-inch wide strips.
Spread strips on waxed paper and let dry for 2 hours.
Drop into boiling meat stock.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 cups.

title: low-fat chicken soup
directions: Melt oil or margarine and saute seasoning for about 5 minutes. Add chicken and cook about 5 minutes more.
Add salt and pepper to taste and 2 quarts of water to chicken mixture.
Sweet basil and a few whole allspice may be added for flavor.
Great with rice or noodles.

title: quick corn chowder
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan.
Add celery, onion and green pepper and saute for 2 minutes.
Add corn, potatoes, water, salt, pepper and paprika.
Bring to a boil, reduce to medium heat and cook, covered, about 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Place 1/2 cup milk in a jar with tight-fitting lid.
Add flour and shake vigorously.
Add gradually to cooked vegetables, stirring in slowly and add remaining milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Serve garnished with chopped fresh parsley.

title: art's special chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Combine first 6 ingredients using an electric mixer. When thoroughly mixed add the next three items and mix well.
In a separate dish mix the next three items and mix thoroughly.
Add to the rest of the mix.
Add the final ingredient and mix everything together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a lightly greased cookie sheet and bake for 11 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: angel fudge
directions: Place the sugar, chocolate syrup and milk in a deep kettle (3-quart) and stir over medium heat until the ingredients are well blended.
Boil, without stirring, until the mixture forms a soft ball (234°) when dropped into cold water.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze juice out of spinach.
Mix all ingredients well. Chill overnight.
Serve with your choice of fresh raw vegetables.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Select a light colored, oblong-shaped eggplant.
They are not bitter.
Peel, remove seeds and cut into strips.
Soak in salted ice water for 1 hour; drain.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Mix your cake mix as usual, adding mandarin oranges.
Bake until done.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift
together	flour,	sugar,	soda,
salt, nutmeg and cinnamon
into
a
mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add eggs, bananas, rolled oats and nuts.
Beat until thoroughly blended. Drop by teaspoonfuls, about 1 1/2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake
in
a	400° oven for 15 minutes, or until done.
Remove
from
pan immediately.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400° to 425°.
Cut or tear the biscuits into 2 or 4 pieces.
Melt butter in a meat loaf pan (for more than 2 cans use a shallow baking pan so that the middle will get cooked). Arrange biscuit pieces on next and sprinkle with sugar.
Press into pan slightly (you don't want to mash all the pieces together but you don't want it too loose).
Bake for 10 to 20 minutes (time and temperature are approximate, check periodically and be sure the center gets done).	Pull apart and eat.

title: double crunch bars
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Press firmly into well-greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake in preheated very hot oven (450° to 425°) for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.
Cool thoroughly; cut into bars.

title: bran muffins
directions: Soak 1 cup bran in boiling water.
Mix together sugar, salad oil, eggs and buttermilk.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to sugar mixture.
Add the soaked bran, plus dry bran and raisins. Bake in well greased and floured muffin tins at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(Will keep 3 weeks in the refrigerator.)

title: pit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: meatless meatballs
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and remaining ingredients except bread. Mix well and add bread cubes. Mix with wet hands to form balls, pressing a little so that bread is no longer in cubes.
If too dry, add more milk.
Brown lightly in oil (Mazola or olive). Drain on paper towels.

title: smothered steak and onions
directions: Sprinkle steak with lemon-herb seasoning.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add steak and cook 2 minutes on each side to sear.
Arrange onion rings over steak.
Combine bouillon granules and hot water, stirring well; add to skillet.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 12 to 15 minutes or until onion is tender.
Remove steak and onion from skillet; keep warm.

title: zucchini fritata
directions: Grate zucchini. Sprinkle lightly with salt and set aside to drain. Beat eggs. Add drained zucchini, green onions and flour, 1 tablespoon at a time, to incorporate into the egg mixture. Add pepper. Heat a nonstick skillet and swirl 1 tablespoon of olive oil. Place 1/3 of the zucchini mixture into the pan and cover over lowered heat until the egg mixture is set and brown around the edge. Turn once and brown the other side. Slide out of the skillet onto a warm plate. Add more olive oil to pan and repeat with the rest of the mixture. Cut into pie shaped wedges and serve with a crisp salad and crusty bread for a delightful summer supper or light luncheon. Serves 4.

title: best ever pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift together the flour and salt. Add flour mixture and milk alternately.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not open oven.
Cake should be very tall and lightly browned when done.

title: hungarian balish
directions: Sift flour in bowl and cut in shortening.
Heat milk until warm.
Add yeast; stir until dissolved.
Mix 3 eggs slightly.
Add milk and yeast mixture to it, then add it to the flour mixture and work until it comes clean off hands and bowl.
Don't overwork. Add more flour, if needed.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Roll on lightly floured board; cut into 2 1/2-inch squares.
Fill with favorite filling (apricot, prune or nut).
Brush with egg and milk mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly brown in 350° oven.
Brush with melted butter.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mash bananas up and mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: christmas cake
directions: Boil mixture of first 8 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Dissolve soda in a little cold water and add to mixture.
Let cool.
When nearly cold, add flour and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
Mix bran flakes and milk into mixing bowl.
Let stand for 2 minutes or until soft. Add egg and shortening.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to cereal mixture.
Portion batter evenly into 6 greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups.
Bake in oven at 400° for about 25 minutes or until muffins are golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: jean's fried pies
directions: Roll pastry to 1/8 inch thickness.
Cut with 4-inch cookie cutter.
On each round place 1 1/2 tablespoons fruit; moisten edges with cold water.
Fold over; seal with floured fork.
Fry in deep hot fat (370°) for 3 to 4 minutes until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Or saute in a small amount of fat, then brown in 425° oven.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix and bake in a greased 11 x 7-inch pan 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.
Delicious!

title: pie crust
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons vinegar with 1 egg in a measuring cup.
Add enough cold water to make 1 cup.
Mix together.

title: musical pie
directions: In a medium saucepan over very low heat, stir together semi-sweet chocolate and butter until melted.
Off heat, stir in cereal (without crushing) until coated.
Turn into buttered 8-inch glass pie plate and spread over bottom and side, not over rim. Chill until firm.
(Chocolate will seep through and make a shiny firm bottom.)

title: pecan pie southern style(this pecan pie is so good!)
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together, then add to unbaked pie shells.
Bake 10 minutes in a 425° oven, then lower heat to 350° and bake for 45 minutes.
Makes two.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add slightly beaten eggs, chopped apples, spices, nuts and Jiffy mix.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugarless salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling point.
Dissolve Jell-O in pineapple.
When it begins to thicken, add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In a 6-quart saucepot, brown roast on all sides in hot oil. Spoon off fat; stir in soup, onion soup mix and 1 cup water. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 2 hours.
Add vegetables. Cover and cook 45 minutes longer.
Garnish with fresh parsley and serve.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well and bake for 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean at 400°.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Add margarine and crackers last.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no-crust egg custard pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; then stir in 3 beaten eggs (slightly beaten).
Add vanilla, nutmeg and evaporated milk.
Pour into pie pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake 50 minutes at 325°.

title: baked apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven at 350 degrees.
Spray 2 quart casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.
In large bowl, toss apples with granulated sugar, lemon juice, 1 teaspoon cinnamon; spoon into dish.
Spread applesauce evenly over mix.
In medium bowl, combine oats, brown sugar, flour, evaporated milk, dry milk, and 1 teaspoon cinnamon;
spread over applesauce.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until brown and bubbly.
Cool slightly; serve warm.
Top with a dollop of yogurt.

title: onion casserole
directions: Shred onions.
Melt margarine and cook onions until tender. Butter a casserole dish and line with cracker crumbs.
Add onions and soup in layers until dish is full.
Beat eggs and add milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over top of casserole.
Sprinkle grated cheese and few more cracker crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbles.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Cover.
Refrigerate 12 hours or overnight.
Mix last 4 ingredients.
Pour over cucumber mixture.
Refrigerate.
This will last two months.

title: party punch
directions: Slice the orange into 5 or 6 slices and put them in a tea kettle. Sprinkle the sugar over the slices. Add the cloves.
Pour the water into the tea kettle.
Bring all this to a boil. Turn off the heat and let it stand for 5 minutes. Add the pineapple juice and the orange juice.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites with 1 tablespoon of sugar until stiff, then fold into batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Make crumbs of flour and shortening.
Beat egg, water and vinegar and add to crumb mixture.
Makes 2 pie crusts.

title: hot corn
directions: Mix margarine, cheese and milk in saucepan and heat until it bubbles.
Stir into corn and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: braised shoulder lamb chops
directions: Trim outer fat from chops.
Heat in a 5-quart Dutch oven. Wipe bottom with a piece of the fat that was trimmed from the meat, using a fork to handle the fat.
Brown chops on both sides. Add onions and garlic, lifting chops so onions are on the bottom. Saute, stirring, until onions are golden.
Add salt, pepper, dill and 3/4 cup wine.
Bring to boiling; cover and simmer until lamb is tender, about 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Stir the flour into the reserved cup of wine.
Skim fat from top of broth.
Stir flour mixture into broth and cook over medium heat until thickened. Makes 4 servings.

title: kidney bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and drain fat; add beans and tomatoes.
Simmer a few minutes.
In large baking dish, place 1/2 of bean mixture. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1/2 onion, sliced thin. Repeat and cover entire mixture with 1/2 pound bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nassau grits
directions: *Use chopped ham for main dish and ground ham for side dish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except for the potato chips.
Bake in a greased dish at 425° for 20 minutes.
Top with crushed chips and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: rainbow salad
directions: Cook rotini until done.
Rinse with cool water and drain.
Add olive oil.
This keeps it from sticking together.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Dissolve soda in boiling water and pour over dates.
Let cool. Cream butter with sugar.
Add egg, salt and vanilla flavoring. Add scalded dates with water and nuts.
Sift flour with cream of tartar and beat in last.
Grease a glass baking dish and pour in mixture.
It will be very thin and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Good served with whipped cream or Clear Sauce.

title: short cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in the shortening with a blender.
Add milk and eggs.
Beat after each addition.
Combine the two mixtures.
It will be sticky but put it out on a floured board as for pie crust.
Then brush with melted butter.
Roll as for jelly roll and cut into pieces 1 1/2-inches thick.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot with berries and cream.
This can be made ahead and stored in refrigerator until time to bake for serving.

title: manicotti
directions: Season and brown beef; drain.
Boil manicotti noodles; blot dry.
Mix grated cheese, cottage cheese and meat mixture.
Place stuffed noodles in pan and pour Ragu sauce over noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with grated cheese.
Noodles will be stuffed with cheese and meat mixture.

title: easy sauerbraten
directions: Place meat in a Dutch oven.
Place all ingredients, except noodles, in the pan in order listed.
Salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a boil, then simmer for 2 to 3 hours, until done.
Remove meat and strain liquid to remove spices.
Thicken gravy.
Serve meat and gravy over cooked noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs, while gradually adding sugar. When blended, add milk, pumpkin, butter and spice.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake an additional 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix all ingredients with fork.
Put apple pie filling in bottom of pan.
Pour ingredients over apple filling.
Take 2/3 cup of melted butter.
Add 1 teaspoon of ground cinnamon and mix. Pour over top.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 1 hour.

title: favorite brownies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add Wesson oil, vanilla and eggs. Stir until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Cook in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: jean's pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast, sugar and salt in water for 5 minutes.
Add flour and blend.
Pour oil over dough and stir.
Cover and allow to rise for 20 minutes.

title: okra fritters
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients; stir in okra.
Pour oil to depth of 2 inches into Dutch oven; heat to 350°.
Drop mixture by tablespoonfuls into oil and cook until golden brown, turning once. Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with salt.
Serve immediately.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Thaw frozen cans of orange juice and lemonade. Seep tea bags in hot water for 3 to 5 minutes and then remove bags.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Bake pie shell in oven at 375° for 12 minutes or until golden brown; cool.
Melt the marshmallows and 1/2 cup milk over low heat.
Take off burner.
Add 5 Hershey bars with almonds; let cool.
Whip 1/2 pint whipping cream; fold into cooled mixture. Pour into baked pie shell.
Whip the second 1/2 pint whipping cream.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread over first mixture.
Grate 1 candy bar; sprinkle over top.
Serves 8.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: * Broccoli, celery, carrots, etc.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Cream the butter and peanut butter. Add the confectioners sugar, vanilla and cream.
Mix with mixer.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt chocolate in microwave at half power or over warm water. Dip balls and drop onto wax paper. Store covered.

title: italian sausage bread(stromboli)
directions: After bread has risen, roll out each loaf separately.
Roll out to a 15 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread butter down the center third.

On each bread rectangle, layer down the middle third the filling ingredients, the loose sausage, sliced sausage, mixture of 3 cheeses, mixture of both olives, green onions and mushrooms. Pull far side over filling and tuck under ingredients.
Fold ends up and smooth, then pull other side over and tuck.
Butter top of loaf.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until top is light brown. Can be frozen and reheated at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: white cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Beat 4 eggs; then pour into flour mixture.
Pour in Wesson oil and buttermilk.
Stir gently until all lumps are gone.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan for best cake.

title: bean casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: italian chicken
directions: Debone chicken and cut into small/medium pieces.
Soak in beaten egg for 8 hours.
Roll chicken in bread crumbs.
Brown in oleo in skillet.
Place in casserole dish and cover with shredded cheese and mushrooms.
Add chicken broth.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Saute meat with onion and garlic until meat is done and browned and
onion	is
tender.
Add
soup, chilies and tomato sauce.
Layer in
pan with chips and top with cheese.
Cook in oven until cheese is melted.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 300° in 4 layers.

title: cherry scotchies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine 2 cups flour, brown sugar, coconut, butter, egg, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Beat at low speed until well mixed.
In a small bowl toss together drained cherries and 2 tablespoons flour.
Stir in butterscotch chips.
Spread in greased and floured pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into bars.

title: bread sticks
directions: Mix yeast and water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Mix oil, salt and sugar.
Add 1 cup flour well.
Mix in most of the rest of the flour and use small amount to roll the sticks.
Roll the sticks as big as finger.
Brush each stick with oil and bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: carmen's flan
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in a blender and mix thoroughly.
In a 1-quart loaf or round pan, brown sugar over low heat; turn pan to coat all sides.
Pour cream cheese mixture into pan; cover with foil.
Place pan in pan of water in oven.
Bake at 350°
for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Invert on plate.

title: pickled beets
directions: Put in saucepan and boil 5 minutes.
Pour over 1 pound of beets with juice and chill for 24 hours.

title: oven baked caramel corn
directions: Measure into saucepan the brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt.
Boil 10 minutes to hard ball stage.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Pour over popped corn and mix well.
Bake at 250° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: red cross fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, butter and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil and cook at medium heat for 11 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add marshmallows, chips and nuts.
Mix well and pour into buttered pan.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: t's potluck
directions: Cook on high, covered. Check often. May have to add water. Ready when potatoes are done!

title: top of the stove meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix beef, crumbs, 1/4 soup, onion, egg and seasoning.
Shape firmly into loaves.
Brown on both sides in skillet in shortening.
Cover, cook over low heat 25 minutes. Spoon off fat.
Stir in remaining soup, water and mustard.
Top loaves with cheese.
Uncover and cook 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
Add tomato sauce, chili mix and corn.
Cook for approximately 5 minutes on medium heat.
In a pie plate press together the biscuits to form the piecrust.
Take half of the package of Mozzarella cheese and spread over the bottom layer of piecrust.
Add meat mixture and top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 - 30 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from oven and let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves:

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach to remove liquid.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, soup mix, onions and water chestnuts.
Add spinach.
Mix together.
Chill.
Good with crackers (wheat, etc.) and chips.

title: marble cheesecake
directions: Spray 8-inch spring-form pan or 9-inch pie plate with Pam. Place cookies in bottom of pan.
Process cottage cheese and cream cheese in food processor or blender until smooth.
Add flour, sugar, salt, egg whites and vanilla.
Whirl until blended.
Remove 1/3 cup of filling; stir in cocoa, 2 tablespoons sugar and milk. Pour plain filling into pan.
Spoon chocolate mixture in mounds over top.
Swirl to create a marble platter.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Turn off oven.
Leave cheesecake in oven with door ajar 1 hour.
Cool.
Chill.

title: banana cake
directions: Dissolve baking soda in hot water.
Cream together shortening, salt and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, mashed bananas, sour milk or buttermilk, flour, vanilla and baking soda water mixture.
Pour into two 8-inch greased and floured pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: the best strawberry cake
directions: Mix water and jello.
Add ingredients in order given, adding eggs, one at a time and beating well.
Bake in two 8-inch prepared cake pans at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge cookies(no bake)
directions: Boil sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes (full rolling boil).
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal, vanilla and nuts.
Beat by spoon and drop onto wax paper. Cool.
Yields 24 to 30.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and microwave with probe 170 on Roast/bake (self-timing). Microwave on Roast/bake for 30 minutes.
Check, depending on microwave.
May need more time.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or 375° for 45 minutes.

title: killer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, salt and soda in large mixing bowl.
Cream butter and sugars.
Mix in beaten eggs, bourbon, buttermilk and vanilla.
Blend in chocolate pieces and nuts.

title: double chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, egg, margarine, water and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until almost no indentation remains when touched, 10 to 12 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: vegetable au gratin
directions: Cook vegetables in boiling water just until separated. Drain. Combine remaining ingredients except butter and bread crumbs. Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole. Melt butter and stir in bread crumbs. Sprinkle over vegetables. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour a 15 x 10 x 1-inch or 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; set aside.
Stir together the flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
In medium saucepan, combine margarine, water and cocoa.
Bring mixture just to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add to dry ingredients.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer until combined.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute (batter will be thin).
Bake in oven at 350° for 25 minutes in a 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes for a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Frost while warm.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan heat together sugar, corn syrup and water, stirring until sugar dissolves.
When syrup boils, blend in margarine.
Stir frequently after temperature reaches 230°.
Add peanuts when temperature reaches 280°.
Stir constantly to crack stage (305°).
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in soda, mixing well.
Pour onto 2 buttered cookie sheets.
Loosen from pans when candy hardens.
Break into pieces.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut flank steak into thin slices.
Fry in soy sauce; partially cook.
Remove from pan.
Cut onions and peppers into slices.
Fry in oil until tender.
Add meat.
Add the beef bouillon cubes to 1 cup of hot water, then add mixture to meat, onions and peppers. Add the molasses, more or less, to taste.
Stir well.
Then take flour mixed with water to make a thick paste.
Add to mixture to thicken.
Add your Gravy Master to your desired color.
Cook on low for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: microwave perfect corn muffins
directions: In bowl, stir together flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder and salt; mix thoroughly.
Add egg, milk and oil.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into paper baking cups in custard cups filling each about half full.
Cook 4 at a time on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Repeat with remaining batter.
Makes 7 to 8 muffins.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Beat eggs well. Stir in next 5 ingredients, mixing well. Pour mixture into pie crust and bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes or until filling is set.

title: baked potato soup(the machine shed)
directions: Add the chicken base and the bacon, heat over medium heat. Do Not Boil.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Beat well.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit, slice pears into quarters from halves.
Slice cherries in half.
Combine brown sugar, curry powder and melted butter.
Layer fruit in casserole dish.
Pour sugar mixture over fruit.
Bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: spiced olives
directions: Drain olives, discarding juice and placing back in jar. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over olives. Replace lid and refrigerate for 3 to 10 days. Turn jar daily. Drain before serving.

title: rocky road
directions: In double boiler melt chips and butter.
Add milk and mix together.
In seperate bowl mix marshmallows and peanuts.
Pour melted chocolate mixture into peanut mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9x13-inch greased pan.
Spray Pam works well.
Chill in refrigerator.
Cut into squares.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to butter mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and mix well.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend all ingredients together at low speed.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
When cooled slightly, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken in pot.
Debone it and put back with the broth, then pour in soup mix and rice.
Simmer with lid on for 20 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Remove from pot and reserve liquid in pot.
Saute celery, onion and pepper in 1/2 stick butter.
Bring broth left in pot to a boil and cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Do not drain spaghetti, but remove about 1/2 of the liquid and reserve.
Dice chicken.
Add all remaining ingredients to pot with the cooked spaghetti.
Stir and add reserved liquid as needed.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Simmer about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: german beef cakes
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes (I used leftovers).
Stir in onions, ground beef, egg, garlic salt and pepper.
Shape into 8 patties. Coat with flour.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and squeeze out all water.
Cook Stove Top dressing as directed on package.
Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Refrigerate about
20 minutes; take out and roll into balls.
Place on
slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into a shallow 1-quart casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° until vegetables are done, approximately 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat the eggs in the butter/sugar mixture well.
Blend in sour cream and flour mixture; add flavoring.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Use a tube pan which has been sprayed with Pam and sprinkled with flour.
I do the toothpick test before cooking the last 15 minutes.
This is a large cake, it will not go in my Bundt pan.
When cooked, let cool about 10 minutes before turning out of baking pan.
Then turn cake over where the top will not have lines across it.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Run steak through tenderizer and cut into bite size pieces. Roll the pieces in flour until coated.
Saute onion and mushrooms until tender.
Push to side.
Add steak and brown well.
Add enough water to cover completely.
Cover with lid and simmer slowly for 40 minutes or until tender.
Uncover and continue cooking until mixture is to desired thickness.
Add sour cream and stir well.
Do not boil after adding sour cream.
Serve over fluffy rice.

title: buttermilk lemon pie
directions: In blender beat eggs; add next 6 ingredients and mix well. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 425°
for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake at 325°
for about 30 minutes.
It is very rich!

title: chicken fantastic
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Beat 10 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with buttermilk.
Add extracts. Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Pour in 9-inch square pan.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and cut into large pieces.
Save stock. Saute green pepper and onion until tender.	Add soup and tomatoes; mix.
Add chicken; thin with chicken stock if necessary.
Layer 9 x 13 inch baking pan with chips, soup mixture and cheese.
Repeat. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
This makes equivalent of one 14 ounce can condensed milk and may be substituted in any recipe.

title: ham ball
directions: Blend together cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add other ingredients; stir well.
Cover; refrigerate few hours or over night.
Form into balls; roll in pecans; eat with crackers.

title: refrigerator cookies(60 to 70 cookies)
directions: Work butter and sugar until creamy and fluffy.
Add flour and vanilla extract and mix thoroughly.
Shape in roll 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Roll in sugar mixed with cocoa and wrap in wax paper. Chill in refrigerator.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins and water for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Do not drain. Mix dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in raisins with liquid and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; stir in nuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: applesauce french toast
directions: Combine eggs, milk, cinnamon, sugar and applesauce. Soak bread slices until saturated. Cook on griddle or frying pan until lightly brown on both sides.

title: chocolate-peanut pie
directions: In a heavy small saucepan over low heat, heat chocolate, stirring occasionally, until melted and smooth. Remove from heat and cool slightly.

In a large bowl, mix eggs, sugar, melted chocolate and corn syrup until smooth. Stir in peanuts. Pour into the frozen pie shell. Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until a knife comes out clean. Cool pie completely.
Brush top with 1 tablespoon of corn syrup for attractive sheen. Makes 12 servings.

title: barbecue
directions: Steam hamburger with onion, pepper and celery. When cooked through, add remaining ingredients.

title: broiler tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Rub butter in baking dish. Put tomatoes in dish.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; take cracker meal, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper and sprinkle on tomatoes.
Dab tomatoes with margarine.
Place tomatoes in broiler for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: lime pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate until firm.

title: emma's peach custard pie
directions: Fill unbaked pie shell with fresh sliced peaches.
Combine all other ingredients together and pour over peaches.
Bake until brown at 300° to 350°.

title: popsicles
directions: Makes 20 in a Tupperware container.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Press hamburger into a baking dish.
Sprinkle with onions. Press into meat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with soup and 1/2 can water.
Arrange Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
May also put a layer of Tater Tots on bottom.

title: quiche
directions: Put in Swiss cheese, mushrooms, vegetables (of your choice) and bacon in pie shell.
Beat eggs and add flour, salt and half and half.
Pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: pretzel torte
directions: Combine crushed pretzels with butter and sugar.
Spread half of this mixture over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese with powdered sugar and add to Dream Whip mixed stiff according to package directions.
Spread half of cheese mixture over crumbs.
Over this, add pie filling.
Cover with rest of cheese mixture then rest of crumbs; freeze.
Take out of freezer 1/2 hour before serving.

title: mandarin spinach
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Remove 1/2 cup of the liquid.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and top with Fritos, potato chips or bread crumbs.
Bake about 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Cook vegetables until crisp-tender; drain. Add celery, onions, peppers and kidney beans.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Put all together in blender (liquids first).
Blend until thick and smooth.
If you want it thicker add more dry milk.
If thinner, add drop of water and blend.

title: dip for fresh fruit
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, and salt.
Whip the whipping cream and fold into cream cheese mixture.
Whip slightly again.
Serve with pineapple or melon cubes, apple slices, or whole strawberries.

title: springtime punch
directions: In a saucepan, bring sugar and water to a boil.
Boil for 10 minutes; remove from heat.
Stir in lemon, orange and pineapple juices.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, combine ginger ale in a large punch bowl.
Makes 16 to 20 servings.

title: hacienda hamburger
directions: Heat oil.
Add meat and brown until almost cooked.
Add onion and celery and cook 5 minutes more.
Add salt, pepper, tomatoes, olives and uncooked noodles.
Cover and cook slowly for 30 minutes until noodles are done.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas with sugar; add margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° in bread pan for 55 minutes or 60 minutes in an 8-inch square pan.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt, sour milk, mashed bananas, then vanilla.
(Add nuts if desired.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with buttercream or cream cheese frosting.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add pineapple; do not drain.
Layer with cherry filling.
Sprinkle cake mix on top. Add chopped pecans and grate butter and spread on top.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Spoon batter into 20 cupcake liners, placed in muffin pans.
Blend cream cheese with sugar.
Beat in egg and salt.
Add chocolate pieces. Mix well.
Spoon 1 rounded teaspoon of cream cheese mixture into each cupcake.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned candied fruit roll
directions: Choose fresh dried fruits when making this confection.
Wash raisins, figs and apricots; shake in a cloth to remove excess moisture.
Remove seeds from dates and combine with washed fruits, pineapple and coconut.
Put fruit-coconut mixture through a food grinder, using the coarse blade.
Combine ground mixture with coarsely chopped nuts and spread out on a flat pan which has been spread with the melted butter.

title: ham-cheese strata
directions: Place
slices
of bread in 8-inch pan and cover with cheese slices,
ham and remaining bread.	Combine eggs, milk, onion
and seasonings;
pour	on
top.
Let
stand
1 hour or overnight. Bake
at
for 1 hour until light brown.
Let stand
a few minutes and cut into squares.
Do not cut immediately or it will be runny.
If prepared the night before, keep in refrigerator. Serves 4.

title: godmother
directions: Mix Amaretto and bourbon or rum.
Serve over ice cubes.

title: lime cabbage salad
directions: Dissolve lime gelatin and boiling water. Add cold water.
Mix cabbage, celery seed, lemon juice, salad dressing and salt.
Add to gelatin mixture.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Stew
raisins
in
water
for
5 minutes.
Set aside to cool. Cream
shortening, brown sugar and white sugar together until smooth.
Add
2 eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.	Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon together. Add flour mixture to sugar mixture alternately with water from raisins.
Add raisins
and nuts.
Drop rounded teaspoonful on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: grilled scampi on a stick
directions: Peel and devein shrimp, leaving the tails on.
Rinse and pat dry.
For marinade, combine oil, wine, garlic, paprika, pepper flakes and parsley in a large bowl.
Add the shrimp and toss well. Refrigerate, covered, for 1 hour.
Thread 4 to 6 shrimp crosswise, on each of 4 to 6 skewers.
Grill 3 inches from hot coals, brushing with any remaining marinade.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes per side or until cooked through.
Be careful not to overcook or shrimp will become tough.
Serve with lemons alongside.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Cut up orange (unpeeled) and apple; chop in blender.
Add cranberry sauce.
Mix with Jell-O and pineapple.
Chill until set.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cut onions into 1-inch pieces.
Position a knife blade in food processor bowl; add green onions.
Top with cover; process until chopped.
Add cottage cheese and yogurt to processor.
Process 1 minute or until smooth.
Add spinach, lime juice and seasonings; pulse 2 or 3 times or until mixed well.
Chill until serving time. Cut off base of cabbage so it will set securely.
Peel back largest leaves and leave attached to cabbage.
Cut off top 1/3 of cabbage and hollow out center.
Fill hollowed out center with dip and serve with vegetables.

title: egg custard supreme
directions: Beat eggs well.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add to eggs; beat well.
Combine evaporated milk and homogenized milk. Heat to scalding point.
Add to first mixture.
Beat well.
Add vanilla; beat well.

title: four bean salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper. Stir until sugar dissolves.
Add green pepper and onions.
Stir. Add beans and gently toss.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled or overnight.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: easy chimichanga sauce(light)
directions: In a blender, puree tomatoes briefly, leaving some texture. In a nonreactive saucepan, combine pureed tomatoes with bay leaf, cinnamon, oregano and beef broth.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; reduce heat to medium-low and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve for sauce over chimichangas or enchiladas.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add peppers and taco sauce.
Heat soups and milk. Layer Doritos, meat and cheese.
Repeat.
Top with heated soups. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mother's rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water.
Stir well.
Add sugar; mix.
Add egg; mix.
Add salt; mix.
Add oil; stir well.
Gradually add 1 cup of flour at a time until right consistency (you can handle the dough without it sticking to your fingers).
Place dough in large bowl and let rise at least 1 hour in a warm place (be sure to cover with a towel).
Punch down.
Make rolls by pinching off small amount, flattening, folding in half.
Place on cookie sheet. Let rise (about 1 hour).
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk and dash of pepper.
In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onions, soup mixture and cheese.
Dot top with margarine and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour; uncover and bake 15 minutes.

title: beef, bacon and bean dish
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef and bacon.
Add onion and cook until tender (about 5 minutes); drain.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil and cook on simmer or very low heat for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Pour boiling water over jello; stir until dissolved.
Add thawed strawberries and pineapple.
Add banana and nuts; stir well.
Pour 1/3 to 1/2 mixture into mold.
Chill until set.
Keep remaining at room temperature.
When set, spread sour cream on top.
Add remaining mixture over all.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line a 12-inch pizza pan with foil; grease foil.
Press dough onto prepared pan. Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool in pan or on a wire rack.
Place cookie crust on serving plate. Spread whipped topping on crust. Garnish with fruit.
Drizzle with dessert topping. Serve immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut up onions, peppers and tomato into bowl.
Cut up meat into another bowl.
Put 1 capful of oil in frypan.
Add vegetables and cover pan and put on low (simmer).
Simmer until vegetables (peppers and onions) are soft (keep mixing and check with fork). When soft, add meat and 1/2 can sauce; mix.
While simmering vegetables, make rice (follow instructions on box).
When all done, add rice to pan and mix and serve.
Add noodles and soy sauce (as desired).

title: rolled cabbage
directions: Put hamburger into large mixing bowl.
Add tomatoes, celery, bell pepper, salt, cracker crumbs and bread crumbs.
Mix.
Make the hamburger into 10 oblong rolls.
Wrap a cabbage leaf around each hamburger roll.
Put a toothpick in each to hold the cabbage leaf in place.
Place into oblong bread pan and bake at 350° to 400° for approximately 30 minutes or until done.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, lemon juice, mayonnaise, salt, celery, eggs, soup and onion.
Place in large rectangular dish.
Combine cheese, almonds and chips and place mixture on top of chicken mixture. Let stand in refrigerator 8 to 10 hours.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Top will be golden brown and bubbling on the sides.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oven chicken and rice
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine rice-pasta mix, seasoning packet, water and soup in 11 x 7-inch glass baking dish.
Mix well with wire whisk or fork.
Arrange chicken on top of rice mixture.
Bake 1 hour or until juices run clear when chicken is pierced with a fork.

title: peanut butter krispies(serves 20)
directions: Melt together butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Add mixture to a large bowl containing Rice Krispies. Mix thoroughly.
Add to a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or larger. Refrigerate, then cut into squares.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute ground beef and onion; add salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients except for beans, cheese and corn chips. Cook on medium heat for 30 minutes.
Add beans.
Pour into casserole and top with cheese and corn chips.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350°
oven.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft. Mix in peanut butter and sugar. Add milk and blend thoroughly. Add Cool Whip and mix until smooth. Pour into crust and refrigerator for 1 hour before serving. May freeze and thaw for later use.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a heavy frying pan.
Spread brown sugar and pineapple over it.
Beat egg yolks; add sugar, pineapple juice and flour/baking powder mix.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake 20 minutes in 375° oven.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Mix meat, salt, pepper, bread crumbs, eggs and onion.
Shape into small balls.
In frying pan, cook bacon.
Drain, reserving drippings in pan, and crumble.
Brown meatballs in drippings.
Pour off grease.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together;
drop by teaspoon into hot grease.
Fry until floating or golden brown.

title: kick the can ice cream(welcome school's)
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour mixture into a 1 pound coffee can.
Be sure the lid is on tight and taped shut.
Place can inside a 3 pound coffee can.
Pack with crushed ice and rock salt.
Tape lid on securely.
Now, roll, roll, roll!!!! for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate crunch candy
directions: Melt chips together in top of double boiler.
Add the chow mein noodles and nuts.
Mix all together and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken 1 hour.
Tear and mix with chilies, sour cream, chicken soup and onions.
Stuff tortillas
(roll mix inside) with chicken mixture.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with any remaining chicken mix and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Have a 1 quart greased casserole ready.
Mix flour and corn. Add sugar, milk, salt and butter.
Stir in eggs. Mix well.
Pour into a casserole.
Place into a 9x13 inch baking dish with enough hot water to cover the bottom of the dish.
Bake at 325° for 1-1/2 hours.

title: shery's homemade thousand island dressing
directions: In a large bowl, combine the vinegar and milk; set aside to thicken.
Add the remaining ingredients; blend well.
Store unused dressing in
the refrigerator; use within 2 to 3 days.
Makes 1 quart.

title: chicken romano
directions: Put oil in bottom of casserole, just to cover.
Trim any fat from breasts and place on oil (single layer).
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Cover with grated cheese.
Sprinkle (heavily) with sweet basil.
Adjust to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tender.
Can place under broiler for few seconds if want slightly browned.
Serve with Spinach Fettucini and salad.

title: sweet lemonade
directions: Squeeze lemons to yield 2 cups.
Mix with 6 cups of water. Add 1 1/2 cups of sugar.
(Do at room temperature to help dissolve sugar.)
Makes 2 quarts.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Stir and blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar.
Mix pineapple, cranberry sauce and nuts.
Stir this into cheese mixture.
Add Cool Whip and heavy cream, whipped.

title: omelette with ricotta cheese
directions: Beat eggs lightly with water.
Melt butter in large saucepan. Saute onions until golden brown.
Mix Ricotta cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Pour eggs into frypan.
Sprinkle cheese mixture and parsley over eggs and onions.
Salt and pepper.
Cover and cook in oven at 250°.
Serves 4.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli spears in an overproof casserole.
Put chicken breasts on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry, if desired.
Spread over chicken and broccoli.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
If softer broccoli is desired, parboil 3 minutes or use frozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut chicken in bite size pieces. In large skillet, heat 1/4 stick of butter. Add chicken and cook 5 to 7 minutes. Set aside. Combine both soups in large pot on low heat. Add 1/2 can of water and 1/2 of peas. Heat through. Add chicken to soup mixture. Put stuffing in medium bowl. Melt rest of butter. Add to stuffing. Mix well. Pour 1/2 of stuffing on bottom of pan. Add soup mixture. Pour remaining stuffing mixture on top. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and cook 10 minutes to brown top. Serves 4 to 6.

title: tabooley (sicilian salad)
directions: In a large glass bowl, place the bulgur.
Add oil and lemon juice and allow to sit overnight.
Layer the vegetables in the order listed.
Cover the bowl and store in the refrigerator until ready to serve, at least 24 hours and up to 1 week.
Toss the salad before serving.
Serve with a hard-crusted bread, cheese and fruit.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In a small bowl, combine ingredients. Beat at low speed to mix, then at high speed to blend smoothly.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: wahanpi soup(american indian soup)
directions: After soaking dried corn and beans, salt and pepper to taste. Boil slowly 3 hours with meat.
Add potatoes and onion and cook until tender.

title: honey chicken wings
directions: Cut off tip of wings.
Cut each wing into 2 parts.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: pecan delights
directions: Cream sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add flour and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chip dip
directions: Mix and let stand overnight.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix with electric mixer 2 to 3 minutes the sugar, flour, Karo syrup, eggs, butter, vanilla and salt. Pour into 1 deep dish or 2 shallow pie crusts (uncooked).
Top with pecan halves. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Decrease oven to 350° and bake 40 to 45 minutes.
It is done when knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Makes 1 deep dish or 2 shallow pies.

title: eggplant
directions: In oiled baking dish, layer tomatoes, sliced onions and eggplant slices.
Shake on Italian seasoning on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Spread with white cheese and bake long enough to melt cheese.

title: pork chops and gravy
directions: Rub mustard on both side of pork chops; roll chops in flour that has been seasoned with salt and pepper. Brown chops slowly in skillet with oil. Drain oil out of skillet and add chicken with rice soup. Simmer; serve with or over biscuits.

title: friendship tea
directions: In a large bowl, combine instant tea, lemonade powder, Tang, cinnamon and cloves.
Mix well and store in air tight container. To serve, put 2 to 3 tbsp. of mix in a mug.
Stir in 1 c. of boiling water.
Adjust to taste.

title: hominy salad
directions: Rinse hominy and drain well.
Combine with remaining ingredients and chill well.
Serve on lettuce.
Garnish with tomato wedges and more mayonnaise, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn cob jelly
directions: Boil broken cobs in water for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat and strain the liquid of not more than 3 cups.
Add Sure-Jell and bring to a rolling boil.
Add sugar and boil for 2 to 3 minutes or until jelly stage.
The finished product tastes a lot like apple jelly.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan.
On top add soup, sour cream and Cheez Whiz.
Mix and pour over hash browns.

title: fudgie scotch ring
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch morsels with condensed milk in top of double boiler over hot, not boiling water.
Stir occasionally until morsels melt and mixture begins to thicken. Remove from heat.
Add chopped walnuts and vanilla.
Blend well. Chill for one hour until mixture thickens.
Line bottom of 9-inch pie pan with a 12-inch square of foil.
Place 3/4 cup walnut halves in bottom of pan, forming a 2 inch wide flat ring.
Spoon chocolate mixture in small mounds on top of walnuts to form ring. Decorate with remaining walnuts.
Chill in refrigerator until firm enough to slice.

title: ruby french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender;
blend well. Refrigerate. Makes 2 2/3 cups.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour, mix well.
Add eggs, butter and buttermilk.
Beat well.
Stir in flavoring.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: fluffy white icing
directions: Combine first four ingredients and bring to a boil until mixture forms a long thread.
Pour syrup slowly into egg whites, beating constantly until cool and thickened enough to spread.

title: new year's cookies(german fritter)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Scald milk.
Add margarine, salt and sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture, 3 cups flour, eggs and raisins.
Add remaining 2 cups flour.
Let rise until double, approximately 25 minutes. Drop by spoonfuls into deep fat at 375° to 400° until golden brown.

title: fantastic pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend well.
Pour onto hot and lightly greased griddle.
When bottom is brown, flip and brown on other side.
Blueberries or strawberries may be added to batter before pouring onto griddle.

title: old fashioned turkey dressing
directions: Heat
broth and butter, pour over bread crumbs.
Combine seasonings	and
eggs.
Bake
in
moderate	oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Recipe may also be used for chicken dressing.

title: "concoction"
directions: In skillet, fry the potatoes until crisp.
In another skillet, brown ground meat.
Drain potatoes and drain meat.
Add potatoes to meat, then add corn, beans and everything else.
Simmer, covered, 15 minutes.

title: cherry trifle
directions: Crumble 1 cake layer in bottom of trifle dish.
In this order, layer
of
all remaining ingredients:
pineapple, cherries, pudding, whipped topping, nuts and coconut.
Crumble second layer on
top of other and repeat as above.
Refrigerate.
Serves a large number of people, at least 35.

title: good cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter in large bowl; add eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla and salt.
Add flour, alternating with pineapple.
Add pecans and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: franks and potato casserole
directions: Brown onion lightly in butter or margarine.
Stir in flour. Add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add grated cheese and seasonings.
Cut franks diagonally in 1-inch pieces. Fold franks and potatoes into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops in 2 tablespoons shortening.
Place rice in long, flat dish.
Pour orange juice over rice; arrange chops on top. Pour soup over all.
Cover and cook 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Place all ingredients
in
bowl,
mix
well.
Pour into greased
9	x 13-inch pan.	Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool.
May be removed from pan if desired.	Very moist cake.

title: rainbow milk
directions: Soften the sherbet in a pitcher or bowl.
Blend in milk with a spoon or a rotary beater until sherbet is melted and thoroughly combined with the milk.
Add the vanilla.
Serve immediately in chilled glasses.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients. Add the next 5 ingredients. Mix well and add 2 cups shredded zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Make sure to grease and flour
pans first.

title: one dish chicken broccoli rice
directions: In skillet in hot margarine, cook chicken, 1/2 at a time until browned.
Add broccoli and carrots and cook until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes, fluff with fork before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim off any fat on steak. Cut the meat into thin strips about 2-inches long and 1/4-inch wide.
Season with pepper and toss meat with 1 tablespoon of the flour.
Melt 1 teaspoon of the margarine in a nonstick skillet over moderate heat. Add the meat strips and saute, turning them to brown on all sides. Remove to a plate and keep warm.

title: oven-fry for fish or chicken
directions: Mix egg and milk.
Soak meat for at least 2 hours.
Heat oven to 500° before putting meat in oven.
Dip meat from liquid and roll in meal or flour.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Arrange meat in pan with small space between pieces.
Spray meat with Pam evenly. Place in center of hot oven; will brown evenly without turning.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; set aside to jell slightly.
Add drained pineapple and sliced bananas.
Pour into long cake pan. Cover top completely with marshmallows; set aside to jell.
Mix well the flour, sugar, butter, egg and pineapple juice.
Cook over medium heat until thick; remove from stove.
Add cream cheese and mix well.
Set aside to cool, then add Cool Whip.
Mix together well and spread on top of jello.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: "light-as-feather" muffins
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Blend in egg.
Measure together the dry ingredients and add to mixture alternately with milk.
Stir just until dry ingredients are mixed well.
Fill greased muffin cups (I use Pam spray) about 2/3 full.
Bake until brown in a 375° oven, about 20 to 23 minutes.
Makes about 1 dozen regular sized muffins.
These are good served instead of rolls.

title: chipped or dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a covered casserole at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: brownies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Gradually add flour, cocoa and vanilla.
Place into a 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at 350°
for about 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Work in shortening with fingertips until mixture has the consistency of cornmeal.
Add just enough water to hold together.
Let rest in refrigerator for 10 minutes.
Roll dough to thickness of 1/8 inch and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Fry in deep oil until crisp and brown, about 3 minutes on each side.
Drain and serve hot.
For a sweet bread, roll in cinnamon-sugar after frying.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Work shortening with a fork until fluffy, add sugar.
Add beaten egg and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Sift together dry ingredients and add gradually.
Shape into roll and chill several hours.
Slice and bake in 375° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: easy fudge
directions: Put chocolate chips, marshmallows and salt in a large bowl. Put margarine, sugar and milk into an iron skillet or heavy pan. Bring to a boil.
Boil a full 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour over the chocolate chips and marshmallows.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: sugarless strawberry jam
directions: Combine crushed fruit and strawberry soda in a 2-quart microwave bowl.
Microwave for 3 to 4 minutes at High (100%) or until mixture comes to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Stir in sugar substitute and gelatin.
Blend until gelatin is dissolved.
Pour into sterilized jars.
Cover lightly and let stand at room temperature to cool.
Cover tightly and store in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: orange candy cake
directions: This is a fruit filled cake, based on a prepared mix.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Form in ball.
Use 1/2 pecans to roll ball in.
Chill.

title: strawberry ice cream pie
directions: Spoon ice cream into crust.
Top with strawberries.
Slice and serve!

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Salt the chicken and cook until done.
Save the broth.
Take the chicken off the bones and put into the broth.
Add butter. Mix together the flour and water.
May have to add more flour or water to make a stiff dough.
Roll out thin and cut into strip and pinch off dough about the size of walnut.
Drop into boiling broth.
Let cook 5 to 10 minutes, add some sweet milk.
Let cook until tender and add some black pepper to taste.

title: swedish meat balls(slow cooker)
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk for 5 minutes.
Combine crumb mixture with meat, eggs and next 4 ingredients.
Shape into balls, about an inch in diameter.
Heat shortening in skillet and brown meat balls. Place meat balls in slow cooker and add broth, dill weed and pepper.
Cook on low for 4 hours.
Makes 3 dozen meat balls.

title: chocolate chip applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and beat well.
Stir in other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.
Top with chocolate chips and/or nuts while warm.

title: rich chocolate layer cake
directions: Melt butter over medium heat; remove from heat.
Stir in vinegar, vanilla and 2 cups water.
Set aside.
Measure flour and next 4 ingredients.
Mix with butter mixture until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Use greased 13 x 9-inch or round layer pans.
After removing from oven, let cool 20 minutes in pan. Remove and cool on racks until completely cool.
Frost with your favorite frosting.
There are no eggs in this recipe.

title: excellent swiss steak
directions: Salt and pepper meat and coat with flour. Brown in small amount of Crisco. Place meat in 9 x 13-inch baking dish, slightly overlapping meat as you lay it in the dish. Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water in pan on stove. Remove from burner and add cold water. Mix cornstarch in small amount of water; add to bouillon mixture. Pour over cube steaks (should almost cover meat). Cut rings from onion and green pepper and place around top of meat. Cover baking dish with foil. Bake in preheated oven at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Remove and serve.

title: cheese cake dessert
directions: Make a basic graham cracker crust.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese. Gradually beat in sugar.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: edible play dough
directions: Blend all ingredients except sugar.
Add sugar and mix well. Knead dough.
Roll and cut with cookie cutters.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together real well all ingredients and form into large ball; then roll in remaining nuts and chill.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown onions, pepper and meat.
Add beans, tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon-pudding salad
directions: Cook pudding according to package directions.
Let cool.
Add all ingredients to pudding.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: cucumber-dill pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Chill until serving time.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mile-high biscuits
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well; cut in shortening with pastry blender or fork until mixture resembles coarse meal. Combine egg and milk;
add to flour mixture, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: shrimp spread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise until smooth.
Spread out on a 12-inch round platter. Sprinkle with cheese, shrimp, onions and tomato.
Cover and chill.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and oil together.
Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon, baking powder and salt together in another bowl.
Add to first mixture and beat very well by hand.
Add carrots and nuts; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 300°, then increase the temperature to 325° for another 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients in the order that they are listed.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 5 loaves!

title: banana split ice cream
directions: Mix together and put in ice cream freezer.
Fill to top with milk.

title: crab meat quiche
directions: Prick bottom and sides of pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, or until delicately browned.
Beat together the eggs, half and half, salt and red pepper.
Combine cheese, flour and crab; sprinkle evenly in pie shell.
Pour in egg mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes, or until tip of knife inserted 1 inch from center comes out clean.
Let stand a few minutes.
Cut into wedges to serve.
Makes 16 appetizers.

title: angel cake with chocolate sauce
directions: Melt semi-sweet chocolate morsels in double boiler with the water.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add egg whites until stiff and add confectioners sugar.
Add whipped cream and nuts.
Gently fold egg white mixture into chocolate mixture. Break angel cake into small pieces and put in Pyrex dish.
Pour half the sauce over and repeat layers.
Chill in refrigerator 24 hours.
Cut in squares and top with whipped cream.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: punch for 100
directions: Mix in 5-gallon can and place in freezer at least 48 hours before needed.
Stir every 6 hours to slush.
Freeze fruit ring of color desired.
Can substitute cherry or other colors of Kool-Aid. Take out of freezer 1 hour before needed.

title: fruit cookie recipe
directions: Sift flour with baking powder.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and Jell-O; cream well after each addition.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture until smooth.

title: hamburger divine
directions: Fry hamburger, onion, garlic, salt and pepper together until brown.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: creamy venison roast
directions: Let roast fully thaw out in salt water.
Sprinkle with meat tenderizer.
Cut up vegetables over the roast.
Cook your soup and add milk.
Place bacon over roast, then pour soup over roast. Cover and cook at 250° slowly for 4 to 6 hours.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: In a large container, mix all ingredients together.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and cut up into smaller pieces.
Take 2 cups juice and mix with 1 package of instant vanilla pudding.
Put in refrigerator to chill.

title: blueberry pudding
directions: Place berries in bottom of an 8-inch pan.
