Sprinkle nuts and 1/2 cup sugar over the berries.
Separately, blend together egg, vanilla, flour, butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour mixture over the fruit and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve plain or with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: caramels
directions: Boil sugar, corn syrup, butter and half of the cream.
Stir in remaining cream while candy is boiling.
When candy forms a firm ball in cold water, add vanilla and nuts.
Put in buttered pan. When cool, cut into small squares.

title: pecan muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
To the beaten egg, add milk, melted butter and sugar. Gently stir in flour mixture until the flour is moistened. Add the pecans.
Spoon batter into greased, miniature muffin tins, filling half full. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until firm to the touch.
Makes 36 muffins.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together and press in a large square pan.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: In a large bowl, mix honey, oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Sift together flour, wheat germ, baking powder, baking soda and spices. Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients and mix.
Add raisins and walnuts. Divide batter evenly in greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes and remove from tins.

title: standard one-crust pastry
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt until particles are size of small peas.
Sprinkle in cold water, one tablespoon at a time, tossing with fork until all flour is moistened and pastry almost cleans side of bowl.
(One to 2 teaspoons cold water can be added if necessary.)
Gather pastry into a ball and roll out on floured board.
Roll pastry 2 inches larger than pie plate.
Prick bottom and sides thoroughly with fork.
Bake at 475° until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes, and cool.

title: the best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Do not use electric mixer.
Cream butter, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips (mixing by hand makes this cookie).
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet and bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: special cookie bars
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugars, then eggs, vanilla, salt and flour. Mix well.
Pour into a buttered 9 1/2 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Spread out.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and about a half bag of butterscotch chips.
Spread coconut on top of chips.
Sprinkle nuts over the coconut.
Cover this with 1 can
of condensed sweetened milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: 7-up torte
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and lemon extract and then 7-Up.
Lightly grease Bundt pan.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 325°.
Cool for 15 minutes, then turn Bundt pan over on plate.

title: special potatoes
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: better than sex cake
directions: In electric mixer bowl, mix together cake mix, instant pudding, oil and water. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Stir in sour cream, chocolate chips, pecans, grated chocolate and coconut. Bake at 350° in well-greased Bundt pan about 55 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix flour with sugar, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Make a well in center and add oil, egg yolks, water, coconut and orange rind.
Beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Gradually pour egg yolk mixture over stiff egg whites, folding gently until blended (do not beat or stir).
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed.
Invert pan on funnel to cool completely.

title: baked herb chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Arrange in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered 1 1/4 hours; serve with hot cooked rice.
Serves 6.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Grease a baking dish.
Cover the bottom of the baking dish with the chipped beef.
Wrap each chicken breast with 1 slice of bacon and place on top of the beef in the baking dish.
Cover breasts with a mixture of the soup and sour cream.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours at 300°.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: simple chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg yolks.
Heat milk to almost boiling and add melted margarine.
Add a little hot milk to egg yolks and mix.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients and stir.
Add rest of milk mixture and mix well.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Pour into a partially browned pie crust.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Melt butter and add shallots and garlic; saute about 2 minutes.
Add heavy cream and horseradish.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer until sauce is thickened, about 15 minutes.
Add seasoned peppers and serve.

title: faye's light pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir the first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes, or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: busy day stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and fry with meat, onion, garlic, celery and pepper.
After meat is brown, add soup and cheese. Stir until melted.
In another pot, cook all broccoli as directed on package and drain thoroughly.
Mix with meat mixture.
Put in casserole dish.
Cook in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: easy cherry-chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs; stir in cake mix (dry), cherry pie filling and oil until blended.
Spread in pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean (surface of cake will be bumpy).
Cool completely.
Prepare pudding mix for pie as directed on package. Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread over cake and refrigerate.
Before serving, spread Cool Whip over top.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together (do not beat).
Bake 1 hour at 325° in pan(s) sprayed with Pam.
While warm, sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top.

title: easy pull-apart coffee cake
directions: Open dinner rolls and pull apart.
Cut into quarters and roll into small balls.
Dip into melted oleo.
Roll in brown sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Drop balls into ungreased angel food pan. Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo to a boil.
Boil 1 minute. Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla. Beat until thick and drop on wax paper.

title: chicken-chili stew
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Cook chicken, onion, green pepper and garlic in oil in Dutch oven until chicken loses its pink color.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chili powder or cumin is not needed for a great dish.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Makes 9 cups of stew.
Freezes well.
(Better if made ahead.)

title: blueberry syrup
directions: Combine the berries, sugar and water in a medium size saucepan over medium heat, bring to boil, stirring.
Bring to gentle boil and continue to cook, stirring occasionally until berries pop and look shriveled, about 10 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice and remove from heat.
Allow to cool.
Ladle into jars.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 weeks.
Can be canned as hot jelly.

title: mamma mia spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti until just soft; drain and cool 2 minutes. Mix butter, Parmesan cheese and egg. Add to spaghetti and toss well. Spread evenly in a Pam-sprayed 13 x 9-inch pan. Brown hamburger, onion, green pepper and garlic over

medium heat; drain well. Stir in spaghetti sauce and remaining seasonings. Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti layer; top with meat mixture. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Top with Mozzarella cheese; bake an additional 10 minutes. Remove from oven; let it set up for at least 10 minutes before cutting. Serves 6.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in an 8-inch shallow baking dish or pie plate and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with Stoned Wheat Thins crackers.
Great and easy hors d'oeuvre.

title: pasta casserole
directions: Boil family serving of pasta.
Once pasta is cooked layer pasta in a casserole dish as follows:
pasta, spaghetti sauce, cheese and meat (optional).
Repeat the layers until casserole is complete. Cheese should always be the top layer.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sangria
directions: In a large pot or bowl, combine wine, brandy, orange juice and sugar, stir until sugar dissolves. Add the orange, lemon and lime slices, the apples and pears and refrigerate until well chilled, 1 hour. Remove from refrigerator and add the soda. Serve in glasses over ice.

title: leftover quiche
directions: Shred cheese and sprinkle into 9-inch pie plate.
Crumble bacon pieces onto cheese.
In blender add eggs, milk, onions, flour, butter, salt and pepper.
Blend for 1 minute.
Pour filling over cheese and bacon pieces.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: three bean salad
directions: Bring sugar, salt, Crisco and vinegar to a boil.
Add beans, onion and pepper; heat just 2 minutes. Store in a covered container in refrigerator.
Keeps for weeks.

title: lo-cal vegetable mix
directions: Pour canola oil in non-stick skillet.
Add all other ingredients and stir-fry until mixture is tender.

title: dried beans and peas
directions: Soak beans until double in size.
Rinse.
Place in 4-quart pressure pan with pork and salt.
Cover with water about 2 inches above beans.
Cook 40 to 50 minutes, according to directions for using pressure pan.

title: amaretto
directions: Boil water, sugar and lemon peel for 5 minutes.
Cool, then add remaining ingredients.
Strain lemon peel.
Can serve mixed with orange juice or pineapple juice.

title: johnny's chili
directions: Brown
the hamburger and drain off the grease.	Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer until hot.

title: whipped cherry surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Use a mixer to whip together and then chill.

title: crockpot casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook on low.
4 - 6 servings.
Stir before serving.

title: jumbo cookies
directions: Add water to raisins.
Simmer 5 minutes; cool.
Mix sugar and lard until fluffy; beat in eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts (optional) and mix.
Add vanilla and fold in raisins with water they were simmered in.
Drop and bake at 350°.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Store covered in refrigerator.
This is great with raw cauliflower, carrots, etc.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Preheat oven to 375°. Cut 10 slices of cheese into pieces.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine; stir in flour, bouillon and mustard.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir until bouillon dissolves and mixture thickens slightly.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Stir in macaroni.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.
Top with remaining cheese slices. Garnish as desired.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Cook rice according to directions on box. Melt butter in skillet; add onion and cook until soft.
Add water, mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz and stir until Cheez Whiz melts. Stir in thawed broccoli.
Carefully add rice and stir.
Pour into buttered dish.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Lightly grease 2 qt. baking dish. Mix together all ingredients. Pour into baking dish. Add more cheese and crackers crumbs on top (as much desired) and spoon remaining soup over top. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: banana bread for diabetics
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix all wet ingredients, then mix together.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 335° for 1 hour or until loaves start to pull away from sides of pan.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
In a large bowl, mix the butter, Parmesan, salt, pepper and egg.
Add spaghetti; toss and coat well.
Spread evenly in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients except milk and slowly add milk to achieve desired consistency.
Cover and refrigerate. Yield:
2-1/2 cups.

title: dessert topping salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over dessert topping; whip with fork or spoon.
Drain pineapple and oranges well.
Add fruit to topping mixture.
Add cottage cheese; mix well.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: blue ribbon muffin or blueberry cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add eggs 1 at a time.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with sour cream.
Stir in blueberries.
Sprinkle top with mixture of cinnamon, sugar and nuts.
Bake in 8 1/2 x 12-inch pan or 16 cupcake pan in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 16 cupcakes.

title: applesauce souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg yolks until lemony in color. Gradually add applesauce and honey.
Beat the egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff but not dry.
Gently fold applesauce mix into egg whites.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart souffle dish or casserole dish.
Place in shallow pan of hot water.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serve at once.
Excellent with potato pancakes.

title: microwave zucchini casserole
directions: In medium microwave-safe dish, cut zucchini and add remaining ingredients.
Microwave on High for 20 minutes.
Stir 2 or 3 times during cooking.

title: chili burrito
directions: Add chili, rice, cheese and sour cream to tortilla.
Top with lettuce, tomato and taco sauce.

title: sugar camp no-knead cheese bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Into a large mixing bowl, pour warm milk, sugar and salt.
Add butter and beaten eggs.
When mixture is lukewarm, add yeast-water mix.
Add and beat in flour. Cover and let mixture rise in warm place until doubled.
Stir down batter and stir in cheese.
Divide batter and put in well-greased bread pan.
Let rise until doubled or to top of pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german apple kuchen
directions: Cut apples in small pieces and mix with cinnamon and sugar mixture and raisins and/or nuts also, if desired.
Let stand 1/2 hour or so.
Mix eggs well in bowl.
Add sugar; mix.
Add other ingredients gradually; mix well. Grease pan well.
Put half of batter in pan, then apples and cinnamon mixture on top.
Put rest of batter on top of apples.
Bake 50 to 55 mintues at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cheese and oleo until smooth.
Add powdered sugar.
Stir in Cool Whip.
In separate bowl, mix pudding and milk until smooth.
Add vanilla and cheese mixture.
Mix well (use mixer).

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat 350° oven.
Drain bean sprouts, mushrooms and beans. Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients except for 1/2 can of onions. Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle other 1/2 can of onions on top; don't stir.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: sausage pasta soup
directions: Remove casing from sausage.
In a large saucepan or Dutch oven over medium heat, brown sausage and onion.
Drain excess fat. Stir in tomatoes, broth and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add rotini; simmer 15 minutes more or until pasta is tender.
Makes 4 servings.
Best if made the day before and pasta added the second day.

title: wonder salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate.
Will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: sausage balls
directions: Brown sausage and drain when crumbly. Combine with shredded cheese and Bisquick mixture fixed according to package directions. Shape into small balls and place on cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pizza (large)
directions: Cook meat in a small amount of water with onion.
Drain off fat and mix with tomato paste, garlic, sugar and salt.

title: fresh fruit kabobs with cherry dip
directions: Thread fruit on 16 wooden skewers; brush with orange juice. In medium bowl combine cheese, yogurt and marshmallow cream.
Beat on low speed until well blended.
Chill covered for 2 hours. Serve with kabobs!
Contains 2 grams fat per serving.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage and onion.
Thoroughly mix mayonnaise and vinegar.
Blend into cabbage mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: sponge pudding
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Mix well.
Stir in lemon extract and nutmeg.
Beat the egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold into milk mixture.
Pour into five 5-ounce custard cups.
Place cups in a pan of water.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix milk, margarine, sugar, salt, cold water and egg in large bowl, then add yeast mixture and flour.
Mix well.
Leave in bowl and cover; let rise.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 very large rolls or 18 medium rolls.
If not using teflon muffin tins, make sure you grease and flour pans.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Arrange pork chops in casserole dish.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Combine the soups and pour over the pork chops.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: german pickles
directions: Mix in gallon jar and stir until sugar dissolves. Add chopped onions and very thinly sliced cucumber. (Salad Shooter cuts them quickly.) Store in refrigerator.

title: hamburger gravy
directions: Fry hamburger until brown and crumbly.
Do not drain.
Stir in flour to thicken.
Pour water into skillet until gravy is desired thickness.
Stir in onion and bouillon cubes.

title: holiday cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg, flour and salt. Add soda to milk and fold in fruit and nuts. Drop by teaspoonful onto baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: twenty-four hour fruit salad
directions: Cook in a double boiler.
When cool, add 1 cup whipping cream, whipped until soft peaks form.
Add to cooled custard.
Gently fold into fruit mixture.
Cover and chill 24 hours or overnight.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak lima beans in water and 1/4 teaspoon of salt overnight. Spill off water and cook in fresh water for 1 hour.
Put in casserole with cooked water and remaining ingredients.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325° or 350°.

title: chinese mustard
directions: Blend seasonings with vinegar.
Mix until smooth, add cream and mix well.
Seal in jar tightly and refrigerate.
Great with Barbecued Pork.

title: pickled beets
directions: If necessary, add water to reserved beet juice to equal 2/3 cup.
In large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Refrigerate.
Before serving, drain; remove cinnamon sticks and cloves.
Makes 8 servings.

title: blueberry cream cheese squares
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar,
water and blueberries.
Cook while stirring over medium
heat	until
sauce thickens.	Cool. Combine cracker crumbs and margarine.
Press 1/2 into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mash
cream
cheese until soft, gradually beat in sugar and vanilla.	Fold
in
topping.
Spread
of this carefully over the	crumbs.
Spread
all blueberry filling evenly over cheese.
Spread remaining cheese, and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill overnight.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; add to eggs. Mix well. Add lemon juice and butter. Mix well. Bake in 300° oven in an unbaked pie shell. Crush Grape Nuts until fine; sprinkle on top before baking (optional). When inserted silver knife comes out clean, pie is done.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Blend sugar and butter until well blended.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each egg.
Alternately add crushed vanilla wafers and milk.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Grease and flour 10 inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer about 20 minutes.
Ready to eat!

title: steamed shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add 5 pounds of shrimp and bring to a boil again.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes or more in juice.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and remove meat from bones.
Mix melted cheese and soup; add chicken.
Pour in casserole dish and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Add crumbled Doritos to top and bake another 10 minutes.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and other ingredients (chopped).
Drop from spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 25 minutes.

title: night before casserole
directions: Spread bread with margarine.
Place six slices in bottom of greased 13 x 9 baking pan.
Top each slice with slice of cheese and ham.
Brush with mustard.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine.
Pour milk over crumbs; top with remaining ingredients and press down firmly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Cool, cut into bars and store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: hot dogs on a stick
directions: Slowly heat oil at least one-inch deep to 375°.
In small saucepan, gently heat barbecue sauce.
Combine pancake mix, cornmeal, sugar and 2/3 cup water.
Beat with rotary beater just until smooth.
Let batter stand for about 10 minutes to thicken. Dip frank into batter to coat all over lightly.
In hot oil, fry franks a few at a time for two to three minutes, or until crisp and golden brown.
Lift out with a slotted spoon and drain well on paper towels.
Insert wooden skewer into one end of each frank. Serve at once with barbecue sauce for dipping.

title: country style potatoes(microwave)
directions: Place potatoes in a 2-quart microproof casserole with water. Cook, covered, on High (Maximum power) for 10 to 12 minutes or until steaming hot.
Drain.
Add milk, salt, chives and butter. Stir carefully, then stir in Parmesan cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Cook, uncovered, on 50.
Simmer 8 to 9 minutes or until tender.

title: barbecue flank steak
directions: Have butcher make a pocket in the flank steak.
Tenderize meat according to package directions.
Inside meat pocket, place a layer of salami, cheese, salami and onion.
Mix together oregano and parsley.
Sprinkle over meat and cheese.
Seal meat pocket with meat pins or hooks.

title: simple summer appetizer
directions: Cut artichoke hearts and tomatoes into bite size pieces. Slice avocados.
Arrange in glass serving dish.
Pour Italian dressing over all and chill for a few hours.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs by hand until foamy, gradually add oil and sugar, add zucchini, cinnamon, salt, soda and baking powder; mix well. Gradually blend in flour, mixing well after every addition.
Fold in walnuts.
Divide batter into 2 loaf pans, greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spicy baked chicken
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in paper bag.
Shake chicken in it.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in 2-quart casserole.
Lay chicken, skin side down.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: taco platter
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix and set aside.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning together; set aside.
Mix green onion, tomatoes, olives and cheese to make the topping.
Set aside.

title: pasta salad
directions: First cook pasta according to directions given.
Mix all ingredients (excluding pasta) together and then mix in with drained and cooked pasta.
Store in the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Beat 4 eggs in blender and then add rest of ingredients.
Beat for 2 minutes in blender.
Grease 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken-almond salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; toss lightly.
Fold in eggs and mayonnaise; cover and chill 2 hours.
Serve on leaf lettuce. Sprinkle with bacon and almonds.
Makes 2 servings.
Can be easily doubled.

title: sweet and sour chicken chow mein
directions: Mix all ingredients except noodles in 10-inch skillet.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender.
Serve over noodles.
Yields 6 servings.

title: apple berry sparkler
directions: Combine apple juice and cranberry juice concentrates; chill. Just before serving, stir in mineral water.
Serve over ice and garnish if desired.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: strawberry dream pie
directions: Arrange whole strawberries in bottom of pie crust.
Prepare whipped topping mix as directed on package.
Gradually add sugar to cream cheese in bowl, blending well.
Add vanilla. Fold in whipped topping and spoon into pie shell over berries. Chill at least 3 hours. Garnish with additional whole strawberries, if desired.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain potatoes and mash.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine in saucepan;
boil 1 minute.
Add
peanut
butter,
vanilla
and oats.
Mix well. Drop by tablespoons onto wax paper; cool.

title: slap your brains out cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; mix well.
Add flour and cinnamon.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle butterscotch morsels on top of batter and bake at 350° for 1 hour in preheated oven.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in bowl, add eggs and vanilla, then add pumpkin, raisins and carrots.
Mix well.
Spray 12 muffin tins with nonstick cooking spray.
Put mixture into muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Add cold water to slightly beaten egg white. Using fork, dip each nut in egg mixture. Sift all dry ingredients together and roll nuts in a portion of this mixture until well coated. Put half remaining mixture in shallow pan.
Place nuts well apart and cover with remaining mixture.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Shake off excess spice mixture.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Mix in spinach and cheese.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until browned lightly on top.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix .
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan which has been lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool cake completely and remove from pan.
Slice cake in 1/2 lengthwise.

title: lujean salad *
directions: Prepare salad as you prefer:
lettuce, tomato, onion, etc. Mix with the remaining ingredients.

title: sweet chili
directions: Add all ingredients together.

title: unbaked peanut bars
directions: Heat corn syrup and sugar on stove until mixture boils. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and Cheerios.
Mix well. Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Put in a greased casserole and bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Place potatoes and water to cover in large saucepan; heat to boiling. reduce heat; cover and simmer 20-25 min. until tender. Drain potatoes; return to saucepan. Mash potatoes until no lumps remain, gradually adding milk in small amounts. Add salt and pepper. Spray Pam into mixture for 15 seconds; mix until blended. Spoon into serving bowl and garnish with paprika, snipped parsley, watercress, or chives, if desired. Makes 8 servings.

title: biscuit topped italian casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef and onions (drained). Stir in water, pepper, tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vegetables and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Put biscuits on top separated, then sprinkle remaining cheese in center and around edge.
Brush biscuits with butter.
Bake for 22 to 27 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: company baked pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in a 9 x 13-inch pan and season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of Cheddar cheese over pork chops. Slice a layer of onions, then a layer of potatoes, then season with salt and pepper.
Put the can of mushroom soup over potatoes and onions.
Then sprinkle the rest of the grated cheese over the soup.
Cover pan and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: layered mozzarella and tomato salad
directions: On a large serving platter, alternate overlapping slices of tomato and Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle basil, parsley and black olives over all.
Drizzle vinaigrette over salad and grind black pepper on generously.
Serve at room temperature.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sandwich puffs
directions: Put butter and water in saucepan and let boil.
Then add flour and beat vigorously.
When smooth, add 1 egg at a time and mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonful on a greased cookie sheet and bake 30 minutes in a 350° to 375° oven.
Cool and fill with ham, chicken, tuna salad, etc.

title: vegelona patties
directions: Combine all ingredients, except gravy.
Form into patties and brown in hot oil.
Serve with mushroom soup gravy made with Gravy Quick.

title: choc-oat chip bar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk, and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips, and nuts. Mix well.
Press dough onto bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake about 35 to 40 minutes or until light brown.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 30 to 35 minutes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Frost with chocolate frosting.
Very good.

title: lemon crumb squares
directions: Blend together, milk, juice and lemon peel. Set aside. Sift together, flour, baking powder and salt. Cream butter. Blend in sugar. Add oatmeal and flour mixture. Mix until crumbly. Spread half the mixture in an 8 x 12 x 2 inch buttered baking pan. Pat down. Spread condensed milk mixture over top. Cover with remaining crumb mixture. Bake at 350° until brown around edges, about 25 minutes. Cool in pan at room temperature for 15 minutes. Cut into 1 3/4 inch squares. Chill in pan until firm. Yield, 2 dozen.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted, then remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and stir until well coated.
Use either a buttered spatula or wax paper to press mixture evenly into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions, but add 2 tablespoons of creme de menthe and some food coloring.
When cake cools, poke some holes into top of cake.
I use a golf tee.
(Clean of course.)
Heat fudge sauce, then pour over cake, making sure to fill holes.
Let cool.
Mix 2 tablespoons of creme de menthe and food coloring in Cool Whip; frost cake, then refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve cold.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar, milk, vanilla and egg.
Beat until creamy.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix until creamed.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Heat oven to 375°; bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add cream cheese and whipped topping.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: oleen's chocolate chess pie
directions: Bake pie shell 5 minutes at 350°.
Mix all ingredients well and spoon into pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and enjoy.

title: cabbage patch
directions: Cook ground beef until done.
Do not brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer at least 1 hour.

title: french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add salt, margarine and enough flour to make stiff dough.
Knead in enough additional flour until smooth dough.
Cover; let rise until double.
Punch down; let rise again.
Shape into 2 long rolls (jelly roll fashion, tuck ends under).
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Let raise until double (watch this dough raises quickly).
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.
After baking, brush with mixture of 1 egg white and 1 tablespoon water for shiny crust or brush with margarine for soft crust.

title: spicy south of the border dip
directions: Melt Velveeta in top of double boiler.
Drain Ro-Tel tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Add Ro-Tel and chili to Velveeta. Stir in Ro-Tel liquid to get desired consistency for dip.
Serve with Fritos.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix 1/2 cup tomato soup with ground beef, minced onion, salt, rice, egg and parsley.
Shape into balls about 1 1/2 inches in diameter (about 16 balls).
Brown in shortening (with minced garlic clove) in a large skillet.
Blend in rest of the can of soup and water; cover.
Simmer about 40 minutes or until rice is tender, stirring now and then.
Serves 4.

title: steak soup(crock pot recipe)
directions: Toss together steak and flour. Brown steak in hot oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat 5-6 minutes. Stir together steak, water and the remaining ingredients in a 5-quart crock pot. Cook covered on High for 8 hours or until vegetables are tender. Makes 16 cups.

title: old fashioned lemonade
directions: Boil sugar and 1 cup water in small saucepan 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice. Cool, then pour into a jar and refrigerate.
To serve, stir 2 tablespoons syrup into 3/4 cup water.
Add ice.
Makes enough for 20 servings.

title: turtle cake
directions: In top of a double boiler, melt margarine, caramels, and Eagle Brand milk over moderate heat.
While this is melting, prepare cake mix according to package directions.

Pour 1/2 of the batter in a greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan and bake for 15 minutes. Cool caramel mixture slightly and pour this over baked layer and sprinkle the following on top: 1 cup chocolate chips and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Pour the rest of the batter over this and bake for 15 more minutes, or until done at 350°.
You can frost or eat plain.
Good with ice cream.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Next cream butter, peanut butter and vanilla until butter is softened. Add the brown sugar, sugar and well beaten egg
gradually, creaming until fluffy after each addition.
Thoroughly blend dry ingredients.

title: cabbage hamburger bake
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat, onion, rice, salt and pepper. Drain excess drippings.
In a 2 1/2-quart baking dish, layer the cabbage leaves, torn into 1-inch bits, meat, rice mixture and spaghetti twice.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: fiori pasta salad
directions: Simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Terrific on all pasta.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Soak blueberries with sugar overnight.
Mix cake mix and melted oleo with walnuts in bowl.
Pour berries and sugar into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drain crushed pineapple and sprinkle over berries. Sprinkle cake mix, melted oleo and walnuts over berries.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Pour pecans and coconut into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cake mix as directed on package. Pour cake over nuts and coconut. Melt margarine and cream cheese. Melt just enough to mix and add confectioners sugar. Spoon this mixture over cake by spoonfuls. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: buddy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl beat peanut butter and margarine until smooth, about 1 minute.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup milk chocolate morsels.

title: kettle supper
directions: Brown bacon in a large pan.
Take it out and dry it off.
Pour out all but 2 tablespoons of bacon grease.
Put 2 cups of diced ham in pan and brown it lightly.
Add the rest of the ingredients and bring to a boil.
Turn fire out, cover and let set for 5 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers or cornbread.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients in medium bowl and stir until well mixed. Heat griddle slowly.
When drops of water bounce, griddle is ready.
Grease lightly or not according to kind of griddle.
Pour batter onto griddle.
Cook until bubbles appear on top and edges begin to look dry.
Turn and brown on other side.
Serve hot with butter and syrup.

title: poor man pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: sheila's party cheese ball
directions: Set aside pecans.
In a very large bowl, combine the remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Mold mixture into the desired shape or shapes.
Roll shape(s) in pecans until thoroughly coated. Allow to chill in refrigerator.
Serve with your favorite cracker.

title: rio grande supper
directions: Brown meat. Drain and add onions and green peppers.
Cook until tender.
Stir in corn, Cheez Whiz, barbecue sauce and chili powder.
Simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with corn chips, if desired.

title: tuna burger
directions: Flake tuna and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Form tuna mixture into four 1/2 inch thick patties.
Lightly spray frying pan with vegetable oil.
Heat over medium heat until hot. Cook patties 6 minutes, carefully turning over during cooking.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Mix sugar and shortening; beat well.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix well and roll out with hands.
Cook at 350° not very long, until done.
Makes a lot of tea cakes.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Combine jelly, preserves, horseradish, mustard and black pepper.
Blend thoroughly and store in refrigerator indefinitely. Serve sauce over a block of cream cheese with Sociable crackers.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. The top will be browned.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
In crock-pot, mix all ingredients. Cook on low all day or on high for 1/2 day.

title: lobster bisque
directions: Scald milk and cream with onion, celery, parsley and bay leaf. Strain.
Melt butter in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Stir in flour, gradually, until smooth.
Add scalded milk, slowly, stirring.
Add salt, paprika, pepper and flaked, drained lobster meat.
Stir and cook over low heat until thickened.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot toddy
directions: Mix all ingredients over low-moderate heat, simmering until hot, stirring occasionally.
Store leftovers in refrigerator for a microwaved cup or two for later.

title: korean kim chee
directions: Sprinkle salt on each cabbage leaf (unwashed).
Mix it well. Let it set outside overnight.
Next day, mix it again.
Wash it 3 times.
Taste it to see how salty it is.
Squeeze out the juice. Once it is salty enough, add garlic, ginger, onions, shrimp, hot pepper, black pepper, garlic powder and sugar.
Leave the Kim Chee out for two days, then put it in the refrigerator for one week or until sour.

title: apple crunch
directions: Arrange apples in deep, buttered baking dish.
Add water. Blend cinnamon, flour, sugar and butter with fork.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender and crust is brown (about 30 minutes). Serves 6.

title: curt's nachos
directions: Brown and drain ground beef, add taco seasoning and 1 cup water. Simmer until water is evaporated.

title: microwave rhubarb sauce
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, combine the rhubarb, water and sugar.
Microwave, uncovered, on high for 8-10 minutes or until rhubarb is tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in pudding mix until blended; cook for 1-2 minutes or until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Serve over ice cream if desired.
Makes 6-9 servings.

title: cheesy sausage biscuits
directions: Crumble sausage into large skillet; add onions and cook over medium heat until sausage is brown.
Drain well on paper towel. Combine all ingredients, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop batter by heaping teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: barbe-cups
directions: Brown hamburger and add onion, sugar and barbecue sauce.
Let simmer a few minutes.
Put biscuits in muffin pans and put meat mixture in biscuit cups.
Top with cheese.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: pasta with asparagus
directions: Peel and roll; cut asparagus into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces. Melt 2 tablespoons butter and lightly saute ham and mushrooms; set aside.
Blanch asparagus in salted water until just cooked, 4 to 5 minutes or less.
Scoop out asparagus and save the water.
Add more water, if necessary and cook the pasta until al dente; drain. Heat 4 tablespoons butter and olive oil; add garlic and cook for 1 minute.
Stir in the cream and cheese and cook for 1 to 2 minutes until slightly thickened.
Add asparagus, ham, mushrooms and olives; cook for a moment.
Pour over pasta; toss to coat.

title: cabbage soup(a real taste treat)
directions: Put cabbage in a pot with tomato juice and add salt, pepper, sugar substitute, onion flakes and lemon juice.
Simmer cabbage mixture until tender.
Add parsley flakes and mushrooms.

title: baked chicken sandwiches
directions: Mix soup, onion and pimiento in a pan.
Blend
flour with 3/4 cup milk and add to soup.
Cook until thick, stirring frequently. Add cut up chicken and chill.
Place 4 slices bread in 9-inch square pan.
Spread chicken mixture on top.
Cover with remaining bread.
Chill overnight.
Mix eggs and milk.
Cut sandwiches in half.
Dip both sides in milk mixture, then in crushed potato chips.
Arrange on greased cookie sheet and top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix salt into cucumbers.
Let stand in fridge for 2 hours. Meanwhile, mix together in saucepan sugar, 1/4 teaspoon salt, vinegar, oil and garlic powder.
Bring to boil.
Cook 1 minute. Let cool.
Drain cucumbers thoroughly.
Mix pimentos and dill weed into cucumbers.
Pour liquid over cucumbers and mix well.

title: boiled cake #1
directions: Boil all ingredients for 3 minutes; let cool.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into loaf pan and bake 45 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.
Prick with toothpick to check if done.

title: mandarin-pineapple cake
directions: Blend with electric mixer for 3 minutes.
Divide into three 8-inch pans and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or use 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and let cool.
Then add pineapple and fruit cocktail.
When jello begins to congeal or thicken, add the Cool Whip.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Combine ingredients and bake until syrup thickens.

title: dump cake
directions: You will need one buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread rolls in lightly greased 12-inch pizza pan, press perforations to seal.
Combine eggs, crumbled bacon, cheese and mushrooms (optional).
Pour over crust.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken rice skillet
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, brown chicken in oil for about 4 minutes on each side or until almost tender. Add celery, onions, and peppers; cook until vegetables are crisp-tender. Stir in the beans and mushrooms; cook until chicken juices run clear.

title: quick crunch
directions: Cook filling for 10 to 15 minutes or until tender. Add sugar to taste. Whip butter until chunky. Add cake mix and stir, but leave lumpy. Grease pan. Put 1 cup of crunch on bottom and add filling. Add rest of crunch mixture on top. Bake for about 45 minutes at 350°. (For extra crunch, use 2 boxes of cake mix.)

title: chestnut-stuffed wild turkey
directions: Sprinkle turkey inside and out with salt and pepper.
Cook sausage in skillet until well done.
Add onion and celery; continue to cook until vegetables are tender.
Add seasonings, chopped chestnuts and breadcrumbs; mix well.
Spoon stuffing lightly into neck and body cavities.
Close openings with skewers and string.
Cover breast with bacon slices and cheesecloth soaked in melted bacon fat.
Pull legs upward, wild turkey fashion and tie with string.
Turn wings under.
Place turkey breast up on rack in roasting pan.
Roast in preheated 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes per pound or until tender, basting frequently.
Remove cheesecloth, skewers and string.
Serves 8.

title: linda's chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and cut into pieces.
Add cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and sour cream.
Melt the margarine and add one stack of the crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pistachio cream cheese treat
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter.
Pat dough mixture evenly on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes to make your crust.
Let cool.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Mix garlic, parsley and mustard into a paste.
Place both tenderloins together and cover with the paste.
Wrap tenderloins with bacon strips and secure with toothpicks, if necessary.
Bake at 420° for 40 minutes or until meat thermometer registers 170°. Deglaze pan with wine and broth and use as a sauce.
Slice and serve.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine and pour over mixture of the first 3 ingredients.
Roll into balls; chill until cool.
Melt in double boiler paraffin wax, Hershey bar and chocolate chips.
Dip cooled balls into melted chocolate.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Melt margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix in separate bowl, the cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour over crust.
Mix in another bowl the chocolate pudding with milk.
Pour on top of cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate until ready to use, then top with remaining Cool Whip and chocolate chips.

title: eggplant salvia
directions: Slice eggplants, tomatoes and onions into very thin slices, no thicker than 1/8 inch.
Arrange in layers in a greased casserole, first the eggplants, then onions, then tomatoes, lightly seasoning with salt, pepper and sage between each layer of eggplants and tomatoes.
Repeat layering until all is used.
Tomatoes should be on top.
Combine lemon juice and oil and drizzle slowly over top. The dressing will penetrate even though it appears scanty.
Bake uncovered at 350° until vegetables are done, about 40 to 50 minutes, basting occasionally with juices that form in the dish. Yields 8 servings.

title: potato dumplings
directions: In skillet, saute bread cubes in 2 tablespoons of the butter. In bowl, cream remaining 8 tablespoons butter and add eggs, bread cubes, potatoes, flour and salt.
Mix well.
Form dumplings into tablespoon-size pieces, then roll into ball.
(They should be the size of golf balls.)
Add to large pot of salted boiling water. Cook until they come to the top, then cook 5 to 7 more minutes.

title: neiman marcus chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar until fluffy. Beat in the egg and the vanilla. Combine the dry ingredients and beat into the butter mixture. Stir in the chocolate chips. Bake at 375° for 9 minutes.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Press crushed wafers and melted oleo in pie pan and line whole vanilla wafers around edge.
Beat egg yolks until light yellow. Add milk and mix well.
Add lemon juice.
It may be runny, but will thicken when refrigerated.
Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tartar until stiff.
While beating, add sugar, one tablespoon at a time.
(Do not overbeat; it will cause the egg whites to go flat.)

title: sausage and macaroni dish
directions: Cook the sausage and drain.
Cook the macaroni as directed. Mix all together.
Makes about 5 servings.

title: dip for relish tray
directions: Whisk all together and serve with raw vegetables or cold steamed artichokes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese in double boiler or in microwave at 50%, 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour mixture into 6-cup mold or individual molds.
Unmold on serving plate and garnish with greens.
If seafood mold is used, ripe olives and pimento can be used for eyes and mouth.
This may also be used as appetizer and served with your favorite crackers.

title: nutty lemon carrots
directions: Put the walnuts on a cookie sheet and into a 350° oven until lightly toasted.
Cut carrots into sticks and steam until tender. Melt butter in a small saucepan.
Add all other ingredients except pepper and heat thoroughly.
Pour sauce over steamed carrots. Sprinkle walnuts over.
Pepper and toss lightly.

title: strawberry-cheese ring
directions: Combine all ingredients, except strawberry jam.
Mix well. Mold into a ring and put jam in the center.
Serve with crackers.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° until slightly brown.
Stir and return to oven.
Reduce heat to 350° and brown.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, layer half of all the ingredients. Layer second with the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and casserole is warmed through, about 30 minutes.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into ice cream maker.
Mix until frozen.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cook together 20 minutes, until soft.
Blend in blender.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl and set into icebox. Dissolve 2 packages of jello in 3 1/2 cups of hot water.
Cool until it begins to gel, then add fruit mixture.
Chill until set.

title: tiramisu
directions: Split ladyfingers or place 1/2 of sponge cake in bottom of 9-inch square dish.
Combine coffee, brandy, 1 teaspoon sugar. Spoon over cake; set aside.
Whip cream to stiff peaks.
Whip Ricotta until smooth; add 1/2 cup sugar and beat well.
Fold Ricotta and vanilla into cream.
Spoon over cake.
Dust with cocoa.
If using sponge cake, repeat with another layer.
(You will need to double the cheese mixture for a sponge cake.) Garnish top with cocoa or shaved chocolate.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour and cocoa together; add to batter.
Add nuts and coconut; beat well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven; immediately spread the marshmallow cream over cake.
Cool, frost and refrigerate.

title: au gratin potatoes crock-pot
directions: Let potatoes partially thaw.
Grease crock-pot with Pam spray. Put potatoes, cheese soup, milk, 1/2 can of onion rings, salt and pepper to taste in crock-pot.
Simmer on low for 6 to 7 hours. Just before the end of cooking time, add remaining onion rings (3/4 hour before).

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil and sour cream together. Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts in a separate bowl. Sprinkle 1/3 of cinnamon mixture into bottom of prepared tube pan. Put 1/2 of cake batter in next.
Repeat until all is used up. Begin and end with cinnamon mixture. Cut through with knife.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: lorettas' italian biscuits
directions: Melt butter, put aside.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar.
Add extract.
Add seeds and mix.
Add melted butter; mix.
Add baking powder and flour.
Mix until you get a dough texture.

title: taco tarts
directions: Brown ground beef or turkey in medium size skillet.
Add taco seasoning as directed. Take biscuits, flatten each one and work into a muffin tin.
Take grated cheese and place in the bottom of the biscuit. Fill each biscuit with meat mixture. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Put all the ingredients, except a third of the bleu cheese, in a blender or food processor.
Blend to a smooth, creamy consistency.
Crumble the remaining bleu cheese and stir into the dressing.
Tightly cover and refrigerate.
Will stay fresh for 4 or 5 days.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Make pudding according to directions.
Fold in other ingredients and refrigerate.
This is best after it chills overnight.
(Sugar-free pistachio pudding tastes great too!)

title: celestial chicken
directions: Skin and bone as many chicken breasts as needed.
Cut in strips, approximately 3/4-inch thick.
Make batter of eggs (beaten), 3/4 to 1 cup milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Soak chicken in batter overnight or a few hours prior to cooking.

title: oven fried catfish
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil and spray with Pam (or other cooking spray).
Preheat broiler with rack 4 inches from heat.
On waxed paper, cover fillets on both sides with mayonnaise (1 tablespoon per 2 fillets).
Roll in dry cornbread mix, covering well.
Liberally sprinkle with onion powder and dust with paprika. Spray tops of fillets with Pam.
Broil until fish flakes easily, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cold vegetable salad
directions: Mix together sugar, salad oil, vinegar and salt, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Marinate vegetables in solution for at least 12 hours in refrigerator.
Drain and serve.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Add walnuts last.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cheese log
directions: Grate cheese finely and soften with cream cheese, then mash and stir well.
Blend in garlic and pecans.
Shape in two 10-inch rolls the size of Ritz crackers.
Roll in mixture of paprika and chili powder.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill several days.

title: sissy's oven-baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, cook and stir bacon and onion until bacon is crisp.
Drain fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, until hot and bubbly, approximately 45 minutes.

title: seasoned potato salad
directions: Sprinkle George Washington's, oil and vinegar over hot potatoes.
Set aside to cool.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to potatoes and mix until potatoes are well coated.
Cover and chill.

title: cookie pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugars, margarine, vanilla and egg. Stir in flour and baking soda (dough will be stiff).
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread or pat dough in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake about 15 minutes or until golden brown; cool. Just before serving, spread cookie with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with walnuts, coconut and chocolate candies.
Cut into wedges. Refrigerate any remaining cookie.
Makes 16 servings.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses in mixing bowl until well blended. Refrigerate overnight.
Form a ball by rolling cheese in the walnuts.

title: no bake drop cookies
directions: Place everything, except oatmeal and vanilla, in a saucepan. Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal and vanilla.
Mix well, then drop on waxed paper.
Allow to cool.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: mexican cole slaw
directions: Mix and heat first 6 ingredients.
Add last 2 ingredients. Bring to a boil and simmer about 5 minutes.
Keeps in refrigerator or can be canned.
Great on hot dogs!

title: grandma tuzzolino's spedini
directions: Pound meat until thin.
Pieces should be 3 x 3-inches.
(You may use a small beef tenderloin roast, sliced thin.
It slices easily if partly frozen.)

title: banana nut frosting
directions: Combine bananas and lemon juice; set mixture aside.
Cream softened butter at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add powdered sugar and milk, mixing well.
Add banana mixture, beating until fluffy.
Stir in toasted coconut and chopped pecans.
Yield: 3 1/2 cups.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Melt chocolate in the microwave. It should take approximately 1 minute. Be careful not to burn.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix milk, egg, salt, baking powder and melted butter.
Add flour until stiff.
Roll very thin; cut into small pieces.

title: fruit pie
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and milk together and pour over butter.
Pour hot sweetened fruit over and bake for 25 minutes at 370°.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: Drain pineapple well; reserve juice.
Add juice to gelatin in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in water.
Heat to boiling, stirring to dissolve gelatin.
Remove from heat.
Blend in cranberry sauce. Add lemon juice, peel and nutmeg.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly.
Blend sour cream into gelatin mixture.
Fold in pecans and pineapple.
Pour into 2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Serves more than 8.

title: glazed wieners(crock-pot cooking)
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Store in an airtight container until ready to use.

title: hanky panky's
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage in skillet. Drain and add garlic salt, oregano, salt, pepper and cheese. Stir until cheese is melted. Spread mixture on slices of bread and bake for 10 minutes at 400°. Let cool and eat warm.

title: barbecue ala lucille
directions: Boil beef over medium-low heat for 4 to 6 hours or until tender enough to shred.
Shred beef.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly into drained and shredded beef.
Simmer one hour. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake in 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 min.

title: steak and potato casserole
directions: In large skillet, melt butter; saute onions until tender. Remove from skillet.
Brown meat and remove.
To pan drippings, add flour, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Cook an additional 2 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms and parsley.
In 2-quart shallow casserole, layer potatoes, onions and steak.
Pour sauce over all.
Cover with foil; bake in a 350° preheated oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: crisp cranberry relish
directions: Place half the cranberries in food processor; turn on/off until evenly chopped.
Transfer to a bowl.
Repeat with remaining berries.
Stir in sugar, lemon rind and juice.
Refrigerate overnight or up to 1 week.	Do not add the apples and celery until an hour before serving.
Makes 3 cups.

title: swedish cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks and flour.
Mold into small balls.
Dip in egg whites to which has been added a small amount of water.
Roll in nuts.
Cut a small slit across top of cookie with a sharp knife.
Bake in a slow 300° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and make dents in each cookie with finger.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.
When cool, fill dent with jelly or preserves.

title: pralines texas buttermilk
directions: Pour into a large pot.
You will need lots of room for the candy to bubble.
The mixture will turn a brownish color.
Stir the mixture until the sugar is completely dissolved, then place the pot on low to medium heat and let it boil to a soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Soft ball means dipping a spoon into the candy and letting a small amount drip into cool water.

If you can form the syrup into a soft ball with your fingers, it is ready. Remove from heat and add pecan halves and a teaspoon of vanilla. Beat the mixture briskly until it becomes glossy and starts to get thick.
Quickly spoon it on waxed paper, making little patties before the mixture (patties) harden.
You can turn the pecans right side up if you want to.

title: turnip relish
directions: Combine turnips, onion and salt; let stand 1 hour, then drain. Combine sugar, vinegar, paprika and food coloring; bring to boil. Add turnip mixture; simmer for 1 minute.
Fill jars to 1/2-inch from top.
Seal and cook 5 minutes in open cooker.

title: denise's prize-winning chicken
directions: Mix together dressing and butter.
Put half of this mixture in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together chicken soup and sour cream.
Spoon onto the dressing.
Sprinkle remaining dressing over the entire dish.
Pour broth over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and water.
Heat oven to 350°. Generously grease pan with grease or butter.
Pour half of cake batter into a medium size pan.
Cook for 29 to 34 minutes.
Take out and let cool.
Cook the remainder of mix while the first one is cooling.

title: snap peas hors d'oeuvres
directions: Shell peas, reserving peas and pods.
In food processor (or blender), combine peas, cottage cheese, cream cheese, cocktail sauce, mustard and pepper sauce.
Blend until smooth.
Rinse and drain shrimp.
Fold into mixture; chill.
Serve pea pods as dippers for cheese-shrimp mixture.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: light fruit cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients except sugar until all fruit and nuts are well coated; set aside.
Cream 1 cup butter with 2 1/4 cups sugar.
Add unbeaten eggs.
Blend with brandy extract.
Add this to fruit mixture.
Mix well.
Put into 10-inch tube pan (with removable middle center).
Bake in slow oven at 275° for 2 3/4 to 3 hours.
One-half hour before done, brush cake with honey or corn syrup.
Cool completely.

title: blueberry vinegar
directions: Place berries in a 6 cup jar.
Bring sugar and vinegar to boil (until sugar melts).
Pour over berries.
Cover tightly.
Let stand 48 hours at room temperature.
Strain through several layers of cheese cloth or soft cloth.
Seal tight with cork or lid.
Use to marinate or cook with.

title: low-fat savory cheese ball
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together the Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and Ricotta cheese until well combined.
Stir in the chives, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and chill in the refrigerator for 4 to 24 hours.

title: the best meat loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients and shape on rack on cookie sheet. Place bacon on top and secure with toothpicks.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Reduce to 300° and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Baste with tomato or barbecue sauce.

title: orange clove ice cream
directions: Combine cream, milk and cloves in a stainless steel or glass bowl.
Grate the colored zest from the oranges into the bowl and squeeze 1/3 cup juice.
Squeeze 2 tablespoons of juice from the lemon.
Stir sugar and fruit juices into the milk and cream. Continue stirring until the sugar dissolves, 1 or 2 minutes.
Put in freezer.
When mixture starts to freeze around the edge, stir and return to freezer.
Stir once an hour for the next 2 hours and then leave to set, 4 or 5 hours in all.

title: onion bites
directions: Mix onion, mayonnaise and pepper.
Spoon on cocktail rye, mounding in middle, but pushing to the edges.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Broil until dark brown and bubbly.
Serve warm.
A regular Kohn family appetizer.

title: moe's salmon stew
directions: Put potatoes, onions and celery in 2-quart saucepan but don't cover with water.
While these are cooking, put salmon in 4-quart saucepan.
Mash them lightly.
Let salmon simmer for 2 to 3 minutes, then add the quart of milk, can of milk, butter, salt, black pepper, ketchup, Texas Pete and teriyaki (if desired).
Let cook on low-medium until potatoes, onions and celery have cooked down to almost no water, then mash with potato masher but not completely mashed.
Add to other ingredients and just as it starts to boil, take off heat.
Add optional potato flakes for thickness if desired.

title: chocolate waffles
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together and bake in a hot waffle iron.

title: shanahan's bar cheese
directions: Melt cheese over hot water until smooth.
Beat in rest of ingredients.
Put through blender, little at a time, using on-off speed on high.
Chill 1 hour before serving.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: pizza dip
directions: Brown together sausage, hamburger, bell pepper, and onion. Drain.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, and pizza seasoning in a bowl.
Line bottom of 9x12 glass casserole dish with this mixture. Top with meat mixture.
Quarter 2/3 of pepperoni and lay over meat mixture.
Top with pizza sauce and remaining pepperoni. Cover with pizza cheese and bake at 350 degrees for about 10 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: good-bye turkey
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chips and cheese.
Heat.
Layer chips in lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Add soup mixture and 1 layer of cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This can be assembled and frozen before cooking.
We take frozen casserole on ski trips at Christmas or save for a snow day.

title: cream nut loaf
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and cream until it forms a soft ball when tested in cold water.
Remove from heat, add butter and beat until it thickens.
Add nuts and vanilla.
When nearly ready to set, pour into buttered loaf pan to cool.
Slice and cut into squares.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown and drain ground beef, garlic cloves and onions. Add chili, Velveeta cheese and green chilies.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Serve with taco chips while warm.

title: great grandmother francis' famous filled cookies
directions: My dad reports his grandparents had to constantly tell all the children to stay out of the cookie jar before dinner! They looked forward to these cookies every Christmas.

title: curry dip
directions: Glop all together and let stand for 1 hour.

title: easy chili
directions: Cook beef and onion in large skillet until beef is browned, drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings; bring to boil, cover and reduce heat, simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. Add beans and simmer an additional 10 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Chill at least one hour before serving. Serve with apples, grapes, strawberries.

title: no fat vegetable ranch dip
directions: Mix sour cream and Ranch dip mix to taste.
Let set in refrigerator for several hours.

title: oreo cookie delight
directions: Crumble cookies over bottom of pan, reserving several for top garnish.
Melt margarine and pour over cookies.
Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.
Combine cream cheese (softened), sugar and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Spread over cookies.
Combine milk and pudding until thickened.
Spoon over cream cheese mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip and garnish with remaining cookies.

title: wendell's brunswick stew
directions: Cook meat with 1 teaspoon salt until done. Cool and take meat off the bones. Cook half box elbow macaroni (8 ounce size) and the potatoes until done.
Mix all of the above together in a pot. Add the peas (garden peas), tomatoes and corn (chop tomatoes in food processor) or to taste.
Put the meat juice in or you can add more if you like.
Add about 3 tablespoons hot sauce or to taste. Add the ketchup.
You can add water if needed.
Cook for about 15 minutes.
Stir often.
Oh! It's so good!

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for approximately 11 minutes at 350° on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: ice cream jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot fruit juice; let cool a little, then add ice cream and stir until dissolved.
Add fruit and put in oiled mold.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Mix together thoroughly the pineapple juice, cranberry juice, water and brown sugar.
Make in a 30 cup percolator.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add soup, Ro-Tel, sour cream and heat. Crush 1/2 of the Doritos in Pyrex dish.
Add 1/2 of the chicken, 1/2 sauce, add remainder in order.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: baked fish
directions: Layer fish on buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix soup with sour cream.
Spread over fish.
Spread shrimp over soup mixture.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until fish flakes easily. Serves 4.

title: corn chowder soup
directions: In 3-quart (microwavable) casserole, combine soup, corn, milks, green pepper, onion, salt and pepper.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 17 to 19 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes, until hot. Add chives and serve.

title: dill pickles
directions: Put cucumbers in jar.
Put dill and alum on top of cucumbers in jar.
Mix vinegar, water, salt and mustard seed in saucepan. Bring to a boil and pour over pickles.
Seal.
Allow to age several weeks.

title: believe it or not pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place in baking dish.
Mix Coke and catsup together.
Pour over pork chops and cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes in 375° oven.
Good over rice or noodles.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Put the rolls on a well-greased with edge pan and press tightly together and up on sides.
Bake at 245° for 10 to 12 minutes until brown. Cool good.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions and saute until clear.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add one cup water and cook slowly.
May be put in crock-pot and cooked on low heat for several hours.
Goes well on hot dogs.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Parboil carrots until almost tender. Drain well.
In oiled casserole, place alternate layers of carrots, cheese and butter. Top with crushed corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: salmon soup
directions: Heat butter and salmon together until butter melts.
Add milk and salt.
Heat to desired temperature.
Feeds 4 people.

title: salmon stew
directions: In a large saucepan or soup pot, clean and place salmon.
Then add milk, water and butter.
Season to taste.
Cook on medium for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour over crackers (oyster), if so desired.
Tastes like oyster stew, but a little meat in every bite.

title: canton chicken
directions: Place chicken in bowl.
Combine 1 tablespoon each of cornstarch and soy sauce; add garlic.
Pour over chicken, mixing to coat well.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in skillet, add chicken and stir-fry over high heat for 2 minutes, until golden brown.
Remove chicken.
Heat remaining oil in same skillet; add onion and stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup water and vegetables to skillet.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Combine remaining water, cornstarch and soy sauce; add ginger, sugar and vinegar.
Pour into skillet; add chicken and cook and stir until thickened, about 2 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: bacon layered salad
directions: Layer all ingredients, except bacon, in glass bowl. Pour dressing on and top with bacon.
Seal bowl with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken with rice
directions: In a skillet, heat oil. Add onion and garlic. Saut 6 to 8 minutes or until onion is just tender. Combine flour and cayenne. Dredge chicken in flour mixture. Add to skillet and brown for 2 to 3 minutes on each side. Add tomatoes, chicken stock, saffron and salt. Bring to a boil. Stir in rice. Cover and simmer 30 to 45 minutes or until rice is tender and chicken is cooked. Serve at once. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Blend sugar, eggs and oil.
Add grated zucchini.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Best when iced with cream cheese frosting.
Also freezes well.
If freezing, frost after thawing.

title: butterscotch pecan pound cake
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese at medium speed.
Mix about 2 minutes.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Gradually add flour, mixing at lowest speed, just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings, pecans and morsels.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 12 cup tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in airtight container. Individual servings:
3 heaping teaspoonfuls tea mix per cup of boiling water.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add other ingredients.
Mixture will look curdled.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 325°.
(This is not a dessert, but can be served with ham instead of potatoes.)

title: covered walnuts
directions: Bake walnuts on cookie sheet 15 minutes at 350°.
While baking, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold whites into sugar and salt.
Add walnuts.
Melt 1/2 cup butter in shallow baking pan. Pour in mixture and bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Stir every 10 minutes.

title: gooey bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and spread evenly in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: bohemian houska
directions: Stir together
2 c flour and yeast.
Heat milk, water, sugar, butter and salt over low heat until butter melts.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add liquid ingredients to flour-yeast mixture and beat until smooth, about 3 minutes on medium speed of electric mixer or 450 strokes by hand.
Stir in eggs, lemon rind and raisins.
Add flour to make a moderately stiff dough - about 2 - 2 1/2 cups. Turn on to lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and satiny, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Shape into ball and place in lightly greased bowl, turning to grease on all sides.
Cover and let rise in warm place (80-85 degrees) until doubled, about 2 hours.
Punch down; let rest 10 minutes.
Divide dough into 5 equal parts.
Roll each part into a 20 inch long rope.
Braid 3 ropes together and place on greased baking sheet.
Twist the remaining 2 ropes together and place over the braid.
Let rise in warm place until doubles, about 45 minutes.
Bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 35-40 minutes, or until done.
Cover with aluminum foil if necessary to prevent excessive browning.
The loaf may be frosted with a powdered sugar glaze or, before baking, brushed with milk and sprinkled with coarse salt or caraway seed.
Or it may be left plain, just brushing the top with butter after baking.

title: creamy squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water until just tender (12 to 15 minutes); drain well.
Add next 5 ingredients.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Use 13 x 9-inch pan or jelly roll pan.
Ice while still warm.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine broth, onion and carrot.
Tie together bay leaf and fresh herbs in cheesecloth bag.
Add to saucepan; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes. Remove herbs.
Dice enough of the potatoes to make 1 cup; set aside.
Add remaining potatoes and 1 can of corn to saucepan. Puree with electric blender in batches until smooth.
Return to saucepan.
Stir in diced potatoes, the remaining corn and half and half.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in pimientos and parsley.
Season with pepper.
Ladle into bowls; garnish with ham and parsley.
Serves 6.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in a large pot.
Salt and pepper. Stir in tomato juice, water and kidney beans.
Add dash of Worcestershire sauce, sugar and chili powder.
Bring to a boil, then turn down to low and cook 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together; pour into dish.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Buy one box mushrooms, wash and drain, cut off stems and chop up fine.
Chop 1 onion.
Using 3 Tbsp. butter saute stems and onion then remove from heat.
Add flour and sprinkle with a little nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Add 2 Tbsp. tomato sauce.

title: orange slice candy cookies
directions: Add the first three ingredients together and blend in the flour.
In separate bowl, beat eggs and brown sugar together. Fold all ingredients together.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
After cool, cut into bars or squares.

title: spicy beef dip
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and garlic until brown and tender. Drain grease.
Stir in the tomato sauce, sugar, ketchup and oregano.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add cream cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Cook until cream cheese dissolves.
Serve warm with dipping size Fritos.
It tastes a lot better than it looks!

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, egg yolks, rind and juice of 1 lemon and butter. Gradually add milk.
Mix well. Beat egg whites until stiff and mix into batter. Pour into a 9-inch pie crust. Bake at 350° until firmly baked.

title: dodge-a-bread
directions: Add enough milk to flour to make a thin batter.
Pour into a greased pan and bake at 450° until brown, about 15 to 20 minutes. Good served hot only.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage until crumbly; drain on paper towels. Spread butter on bread and place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle sausage on bread, then cheese on sausage. Combine eggs, half and half and spices. Beat well; pour over cheese. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate frosty
directions: Mix in a gallon ice cream freezer.
Takes about 30 minutes to make.

title: ultimate chocolate brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, or two square pans, 8 x 8 x 2-inch. In medium bowl, combine cocoa and baking soda. Blend in 1/3 cup
melted butter. Add boiling water; stir until mixture thickens.

Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3 cup melted butter. Stir until smooth. Add flour, vanilla and salt; blend completely. Stir in chocolate chips. Pour into prepared pan(s). Bake 35 to 40 minutes for rectangular pan, 30 to 35 minutes for square pans or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan. Cool completely in pan(s). Frost with One-Bowl Buttercream Frosting. Cut into squares. Makes about 3 dozen brownies.

title: momma's baked zucchini
directions: Brown meat in a skillet, drain.
Place the other ingredients in a saucepan and cook until tender.
Pour the mixture in a casserole pan and mix the ground meat in the mixture; stir well. Sprinkle the cheese on top of the casserole and put in the oven. Bake at 350° until the cheese is melted.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak apricots 1/2 hour.
Drain and grind.
Beat eggs until light.
Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt.
Add alternately with orange juice and water.
Add nuts and apricots. Mix well.
Pour batter into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Beat eggs and flour together; add cottage cheese, cheese and spinach and place in buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meggie's favorite chicken cordon bleu
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Pound breast until thin, sprinkle with parsley.
Top with cheese and ham.
Roll up tightly.
Stir together mayo and water in shallow dish.
Roll each chicken fillet in mayo mixture, then bread crumbs.
Arrange chicken rolls seam down on baking sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until cooked through. Heat soup and water.
Pour over chicken just before serving. Makes 258 calories with 14 gm. fat, 1/3 bread, 4 lean meat, 1/2 fat food exchange.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent roll dough on cookie sheet with sides slightly high.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes; cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and seasonings until smooth.
Spread on top of cooled crust.
Layer your choice of fresh vegetables on top (chopped broccoli, cauliflower, snipped chives, sliced green peppers, etc.). Yield:
16 slices.

title: turkey or chicken tater tot casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in a large casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Melt 12-ounce package of chocolate chips and 1/2 block of paraffin in double boiler.
Dip candy balls, leaving the "eye."
Put on wax paper to cool.

title: bar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine while heating oven.
