Combine graham cracker crumbs with margarine. Press on bottom of pan. Sprinkle with layer of nuts, chocolate chips and coconut.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over coconut. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool. Cut into bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: cranberry-mandarin salad
directions: Drain mandarin oranges.
Set mandarin juice aside.
Heat gelatin, sugar, salt and mandarin juice until gelatin dissolves. Add lemon juice, cranberry sauce, mandarin oranges, celery and pecans.
Put into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook the hamburger meat until done then drain and add all other ingredients; cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti noodles.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Mix together and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: shortbread toffee squares
directions: Cream 1/2 stick butter with four tablespoons sugar.
Blend in flour.
Spread onto greased 8-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix together the next four ingredients and cook, stirring until mixture leaves the sides of the pan.
Add vanilla. Pour over shortbread.
Cool.
Spread melted chocolate over toffee. Cool.
Cut into squares.
Yield:
About 12.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Mix all together and one cup of broth from chicken.
Add salt and hot sauce to taste.
Cook on low heat for one hour.

title: peanut butter bumps
directions: In a medium bowl, mix all of the ingredients together.
Cover and chill in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Roll into 1-inch balls and serve.
Makes 30 balls.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese together.
Separately mix strawberries, pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread in a buttered 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Freeze.
Thaw 15 to 20 minutes before serving.
Keeps a long time in freezer.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add honey and beaten egg yolks.
Add remaining dry ingredients.
Mix alternately with milk.
Stir in fruits and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: fresh vegetables in garlic sauce with pasta
directions: Cut carrots and zucchini lengthwise into thin slices with vegetable peeler. Bring 1 inch water to a boil in medium saucepan. Add carrots and zucchini. Cook until crisp tender. Remove from saucepan and drain; set aside. Melt butter in same saucepan over medium heat. Add onion and garlic; cook until tender. Gradually stir in broth, cream and seasonings; simmer 5 minutes or until sauce in slightly thickened. Add vegetables; heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally. Add vegetables and sauce to hot cooked pasta; toss lightly.

title: rack of lamb
directions: Rub the minced garlic over the top of your rack of lamb. Sprinkle generously with rosemary, salt and lemon pepper.
Roast in a preheated oven at 375° for 30 minutes if you like your lamb rare; 45 minutes if you like it done well.
(We cook it 45 minutes.)

title: sun tea without the sun
directions: Bring 1/2 gallon water to a boil.
Pour over the tea bags and let set at least one hour.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: poppy seed nut bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first four ingredients.
In another bowl, beat eggs with milk, oil and vanilla until blended. Stir liquids into dry ingredients until smooth.
Mix in the nuts. Pour batter into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until loaves test done.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Remove to racks to finish cooling.
Freezes well.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Melt cheeses, butter and milk in saucepan.
Place hash browns in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour cheese mixture over top of hash browns.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barley-stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Place cabbage leaves in a large bowl.
Cover with boiling water.
Set aside. Bring 2 cups of water to a boil in medium saucepan.
Stir barley into boiling water.
Cover.
Simmer about 1 hour or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Drain.
Cook onion and garlic in oil in skillet until tender.
Add spinach.
Cook and stir 1 minute.

title: baked beans
directions: Empty beans into large baking pan.
Stir in mustard, barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Lay strips of raw bacon across top gently.
Bake in a 350° oven until bacon is done.

title: banana-pineapple slush
directions: Mix and freeze all ingredients except 7-Up. Add 7-Up when partially thawed.

title: to die for chicken
directions: Mix all together (4 items) and pour over chicken and dot with butter.
Cover pan with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove foil and baste chicken and bake about another 1/2
hour to cook sauce down and thicken.
Serve with rice.

title: italian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, oregano and garlic powder.
Dip chicken in egg and flour.
Coat well.
Heat oil. Brown chicken; put chicken in 9 x 13-inch (or smaller) pan.
Mix Ragu with mushrooms and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with oregano and top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve with your favorite Italian pasta.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Butter a casserole dish.
Layer prepared broccoli, chicken and cooked noodles.
Mix the sour cream, cream of chicken soup, pimento, onion, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over broccoli, chicken and noodles.
Top with bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: lumpia
directions: Mix ingredients together in a large bowl.
Place two tablespoons of mixture in each wrapper and fold up as you would an eggroll.
Deep fry each in oil, on medium heat, until golden brown.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: In top of double boiler, over boiling water, heat butter and chocolate, stirring until melted and well blended.
Allow to cool slightly.
Blend syrup, sugar, salt and vanilla into beaten eggs. Add chocolate mixture; blend well.
Pour mixture into pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until pie is almost but not quite firm when shaken.

title: gingersnaps(these are crispy on the edges but soft in the center)
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, brown sugar, egg and molasses. Blend in remaining ingredients, except for granulated sugar. Cover and chill for one hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Dip tops into granulated sugar. Place balls, sugar side up, 3 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.

title: mexican cheese bites
directions: Mix baking mix, sour cream, egg and chilies.
Stir in cheese. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful about 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with taco sauce or salsa as desired.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: georgia squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling salted water, 5 minutes. Drain well.
Combine soup, sour cream and carrots and fold into squash-onion mix.
Combine stuffing mix and margarine.
Spread half of stuffing mix in bottom of 12 x 7 x 2-inch casserole.
Spoon vegetable mix over and top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: fluffy boiled icing
directions: In double boiler over boiling water, beat together sugar, salt, egg whites, corn syrup and water until mixture holds stiff peaks. Remove from heat; beat in vanilla.
Yield:
Enough to cover 3 layer cake.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Mix at room temperature.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and then egg.
Cream thoroughly. Add salt, vanilla, baking powder and carrots.
Mix well.
Mix in flour.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: hot butter pineapple punch
directions: In large saucepan, combine and bring to a boil the first 4 ingredients, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Reduce heat and stir in wine, heating but not boiling.
Serve with a pat of butter floating on top and a cinnamon stick stirrer.

title: raised donuts
directions: Crumble yeast into small bowl.
Add lukewarm water and 1 teaspoon sugar; set in warm place.
Combine shortening, salt and sugar in large bowl.
Add scalded milk.
Stir until shortening is melted.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture and eggs.
Add part of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour.
Knead dough until smooth.
Cover.
Raise until double bulk.
Roll out until 1/2-inch thick.
Cut.
Place on greased pan 1 inch apart.
Let raise.
Fry in deep, hot grease.

title: luscious pineapple delight
directions: Bake yellow cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan as directed, about 20 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Beat together the ice cold milk, pudding and cream cheese until thick.
Spread over cold cake.
Drain pineapple well and spread over pudding-cheese mixture.
Top with room temperature Cool Whip.
Sprinkle on nuts. Refrigerate for 4 to 6 hours.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Saute onion in margarine.
Drain broccoli and add to onion.
Add milk, cheese, rice and soup.
Mix well.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: brenda's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with spoon.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Cut and enjoy.

title: lentil loaf
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: italian love cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan (Pam spray works too!).
Mix cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Pour over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.
Cool completely and frost.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli; saute onion in butter.
Mix onion, milk, soup and Cheez Whiz together.
Fold in rice and broccoli. Pour in a large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter until transparent and then place in casserole dish.
Add corn, salt and sour cream; mix thoroughly.
Cook in moderate oven for 20 minutes.
(Cream must not boil.)
Sprinkle very crisp bacon over top of casserole when ready to serve.

title: pumpkin bread rounds
directions: Combine all ingredients and knead into a dough.
Pull off small balls of dough.
Form into patties.
Deep fry the small round balls in oil until golden brown.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Make the chocolate cake as per directions on box.
When cake is done, poke holes in the top with a wooden spoon handle.
Pour the sweetened condensed milk and caramel ice cream topping over the cake.
Cool cake.
Top with the Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.
Keep refrigerated.

title: no-fail french bread
directions: Combine warm water with sugar, oil and salt.
Sprinkle yeast over mixture.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Let rise 10 minutes; stir down.
Continue rising dough 10 minutes, then stirring down every 10 minutes for 1 hour.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
Roll jelly-roll style to make loaf.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: lemon sheet cake
directions: Mix margarine, flour, sugar and 1/2 cup nuts together like cookie dough.
Press evenly in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Mix the cream cheese with powdered sugar and 1/2 container of Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Make lemon pie filling as directed on box, but only use sugar amount per 1 box.
Cool and spread over cheese layer.
Top with remainder of Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: blueberry-peach salad
directions: In large bowl, combine milk, water and lemon rind; mix well. Add pudding and beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon 2 cups pudding mixture in bowl; add cake cubes, then peaches, ending with pudding mixture on top.
Put blueberries around the edges.

title: oven-toasted pecans
directions: Combine all ingredients except salt; mix well.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Drain on paper towel; add salt to taste.

title: broccoli with cheese sauce
directions: Partially cook broccoli.
Grate Cheddar cheese.
Spray a 1 1/2-quart casserole with nonstick cooking spray.
Place broccoli in casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients together in a small bowl.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with Pepperidge Farm crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sue's piggy pudd'n pie
directions: Cut first 3 ingredients together.
Press dough into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until brown. Remove and let cool.
Mix 1 cup Cool Whip with cream cheese and powdered sugar. Spread over cooled crust.

title: home style dressing from mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in small bowl until evenly distributed.
Put mixture in a foil packet or 1-pint glass jar. Store in cool, dry place.
Use within 6 months.
Makes about 2 tablespoons of dressing mix, enough for 2 cups home style dressing.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and set aside.
Cook chicken breasts, remove skin and bones after cooking.
Layer the cooked chicken and cooked broccoli in 9 x 13-inch dish. Mix cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice together, then spread over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle grated cheese over mixture.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: summer cooler
directions: In pitcher, combine grape juice or wine, sugar and lemon juice.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Just before serving, add club soda and fruit garnish.
Serves 8.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in buttered casserole.

title: strawberry lush(or peach)
directions: Mix and press in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Brown in oven and let cool.

title: jezebel's appetizer
directions: Mix preserves, horseradish, dry mustard and ground pepper together.
Store in container and refrigerate (can be stored for 8 weeks).
Ladle over 8 ounce block of Philadelphia cream cheese. To serve, spread on Wheatsworth crackers.

title: sugar doughnuts
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs; beat well.
Add milk with soda.
Add flour with baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
(Use enough flour to handle easily.)
Roll on floured board and cut out.
Fry in deep fat.

title: mrs. wilbur's fruit salad
directions: Mix everything together and refrigerate for awhile so flavors blend.

title: beef ball
directions: Take dried beef and put in blender and shred.
Divide into thirds.
Mix 2/3 of dried beef with cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Shape into ball and roll in remaining 1/3 of dried beef, covering entire ball.
Chill and serve with crackers. Best if made the night before.

title: pink punch
directions: Combine ingredients and serve.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Cook
chicken.
Cut
in strips or chunks.
Mix together lettuce, coleslaw mix, green onions, Mandarin oranges, chicken and nuts.
Prepare
Chinese
Chicken
Salad Dressing and toss with salad.
Makes 7 to 9 servings.

title: popcorn bars
directions: Pop corn in popper.
Melt oleo and marshmallows.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture over popcorn in bowl, stirring the popcorn to mix well.
Press into a buttered 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Melt chocolate and spread over top.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: chuck wagon soup
directions: Saute the onions and pepper in fat; add potatoes, tomatoes, chili, macaroni and water.
Heat until hot and well blended.
Hot dogs or bologna may be added if so desired.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix well.
Pour in glass jar and refrigerate.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Use very large Tupperware bowl to mix and store.
Mix well. Add to hot water to taste.

title: rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 12-cup fluted tube pan or Bundt pan.
In a large bowl, blend cake ingredients until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Combine sugar, peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Use a 1/2 teaspoon to roll batter into balls.
Chill very well.
When cold, melt chocolate.
Dip each ball into the melted chocolate; set on waxed paper to harden.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chopped broccoli and drain well.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter and Velveeta cheese, then stir mixture into drained broccoli.
Crush crackers; melt other 1/2 stick butter and mix together.
Line a casserole dish with 1/2 cracker mixture.
Pour broccoli mixture into casserole and top with remaining cracker mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesy pizza dinner
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Heat thoroughly.

title: beef potato soup
directions: Brown beef in hot 2-quart saucepan.
Turn carefully as needed to brown on all sides.
Keep meat in chunks.
Drain fat.
Add water, onion, celery and seasonings to beef.
Bring to boiling point, then reduce heat and cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Add potatoes, carrots and parsley.
Cook until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and cloves before serving. Makes 4 servings (about 1 1/4 cups each).

title: angel biscuits
directions: (May use 2 cups soy milk mixed with 4 tablespoons vinegar instead of buttermilk.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine eggs, soup, cheese and mayonnaise. Fold in broccoli and put into a 2-quart casserole. Mix crackers and butter, sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: easter egg bake
directions: Trim bread; cube and put in a 9 x 13 greased pan. Fry bacon and drain. Beat eggs, milk, onion salt and garlic salt. Pour over bread cubes. Add Velveeta cheese and top with bacon. Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350° and an additional 15 minutes uncovered.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: In a medium bowl with a fork, beat eggs slightly.
Stir in corn syrup, sugar and vanilla just until blended.
Stir in chocolate pieces and pecans and pour into pie shell.
Bake in a preheated 375°
oven for 45 to 50 minutes, or until a knife inserted halfway between the outside and center comes out clean. Cool on a wire rack.

title: yum yum pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with cracker crumbs.
Line bottom of large Pyrex dish with 1/2 of crumbs.
Beat together Dream Whip and milk. Soften cream cheese and sugar.
Put cheese and sugar mixture in the Dream Whip mixture. Put 1/2 of this on crust and spread pie filling on this.
Add remaining Dream mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top.
Chill.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and shortening together. Add sugar and cream and mix well. Mix beaten eggs, baking soda dissolved in buttermilk and vanilla. Add this to butter mixture and mix well.

title: irish bread
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add egg and blend with milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix by hand.
Add raisins.
Mix by hand.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: southern beef stew
directions: Place the meat in a slow cooker.
Toss with flour, salt and pepper.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir to mix well.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours or on high for 4 to 6 hours.
Stir before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: deer tenderloin teriyaki
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together, pour over tenderloins and let marinate for several hours.
Drain and place on a rack over a shallow pan 4 inches under the broiler element.
Broil 12 to 15 minutes.
Slice and serve with rice and vegetables.

title: lemon macaroon muffin puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In small bowl, beat the egg until light and pale yellow. Add the butter, sugar, salt, vanilla, and lemon juice. Mix well. Stir in the coconut. Spoon about 2 tablespoons of the lemon macaroon mixture on top of each muffin half, spread it to cover the top. Place the halves on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until the topping puffs and turns golden brown. Best served warm. Serves 6.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients.
Line pan with foil.
Toss wings in sauce and place in a large pan lined with foil.
Cook at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Turn wings every 20 minutes and add sauce. Want wings to be brown when done.

title: crusty cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in deep dish.
Mix together flour, baking powder, sugar and milk.
Pour over melted oleo; do not stir.
Pour 1 can of fruit with juice over mixture.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: risi bisi or rice valencienne
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until lightly browned.
Stir in rice, ham and bay leaf.
Saute about 5 minutes, stirring often. Combine rice mixture with stock, salt and pepper; stir well. Bring to a boil.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until rice is done.
Remove bay leaf.
Heat peas, pimentos and mushrooms.
Add to rice; toss lightly with fork to combine.
Cover and heat for 3 to 4 minutes longer.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Use a large bowl.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Slowly add sugar and beat well.
Add oil and vanilla.
Add Zucchini, sift dry ingredients and add nuts and chips.
Bake in three medium or 2 large size bread pans-greased floured for one hour and 10 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for 1 hour.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Combine beef, pork, veal, bread crumbs, garlic, pepper, eggs, milk, basil and parsley.
Mix well.
Shape mixture into meat balls, 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Preheat ungreased skillet for 3 minutes over medium heat.
Saute meat balls until evenly browned. Remove as they brown and add to hot spaghetti sauce.
With meat balls in spaghetti sauce, simmer, covered, over low heat for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Cut pocket in center of each pork chop.
Mix ingredients and stuff into each pork chop.
Fasten with toothpicks and brown in skillet.
Place in shallow pan and bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all four ingredients together.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix flour and sugar before putting into milk and eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 400°, then turn oven down to 350° until done.

title: vanilla carob cake
directions: Beat together eggs and butter; then add mashed bananas and milk until creamy.
Add vanilla, flour, carob powder, baking powder and baking soda.
Beat well.
Stir in coconut.
Spoon evenly into oiled and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.
Cool.

title: ice cream crunch pie
directions: Melt butter in heavy pan.
Remove from heat, using electric beater, beat marshmallow topping into melted butter.
Add Rice Krispies and stir until coated.
Press into 9-inch pie pan.
Freeze 1 hour or longer, and fill with softened ice cream, refreeze until serving time.
Can be served with any kind of topping desired, or fresh fruit.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon.
Use drippings to saute onion in.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish; top with crumbled bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until most of liquid is gone and beans are bubbly.

title: porcupine meatballs(no quills inside this one!)
directions: Combine meat, rice, egg, parsley, onion, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup tomato soup.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into about 20 to 25 balls and place in a casserole dish.
Mix remaining soup, water, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Spoon sauce over meatballs while baking. Serve over noodles.

title: hot turkey wings
directions: Rinse turkey.
Place in casserole or Dutch oven.
Combine taco seasoning mix and water, pour over turkey.
Cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove cover; turn turkey over.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour more.
Serve with sour cream.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: ricotta cookies
directions: Cream together butter and Ricotta cheese.
Add vanilla, sugar and egg and beat together.
Add flour and baking soda.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Drop by rounded cookie dough scooper.
Frost with confectioners sugar frosting or cream cheese frosting.

title: refrigerator strawberry shortcake
directions: Sprinkle mixture into pie plate. Add 1 cup strawberries (fresh or frozen). Add remainder of vanilla wafer crumbs to strawberries Let chill for as long as possible in refrigerator.

title: good pizza
directions: Drain mushrooms.
Keep liquid and add water, if needed, to equal 1/2 cup.
Add breadcrumbs, egg, salt and pepper; let stand 5 minutes.
Add ground chuck, oregano and 1/2 mushrooms; mix lightly.
In a pizza pan, form a "meat" crust.
Cut 2 slices of cheese into 8 pieces.
Layer over meat.
Top with pizza sauce, onion, pepper, tomatoes and rest of mushrooms.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Top with rest of cheese; bake 5 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: onion meat balls
directions: Mix in large bowl hamburger, crumbs, eggs, milk and salt. Shape into small balls and brown on all sides.
Place in saucepan and add onion soup (no water) and simmer for 15 minutes.
Make rice as package directions.
Place rice on large plate or bowl and place meat balls on top.
Meat balls can be placed in crock-pot on low heat all day.

title: meg's roll-up surprise
directions: Lightly cook spinach; squeeze out all water.
Put in big bowl. Add Ricotta cheese, Romano cheese, 2 eggs, basil, parsley, pepper and oil and mix thoroughly.
Cook lasagna noodles until soft (12 to 15 minutes); drain noodles and cool.
Spread 3 tablespoons of filler on noodles.
From short side, start to roll tightly.
Put in pan that has about 1/2 cup sauce on bottom.
Do all the roll-ups and cover the tops with the rest of the spaghetti sauce. Cook in 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Drain pineapple and mix together.
Place in graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Quick and easy. "$Million $Dollar Taste."

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar, stirring constantly over medium heat for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and stir until melted.
Add milk.
Cook over medium heat until sauce comes to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and salt. Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. To mixture, add bacon, fried until crisp, using about 1/2 of bacon grease.
Pour into casserole dish. Cover and bake at 350° for
1 hour.

title: crock-pot corn chowder
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Blend all ingredients in crock-pot on high for 1 hour and on low for 2 to 3 hours.
(I use 1 can of potato soup and cook about 5 cubed potatoes and add instead of second can of soup.)

title: herb croutons
directions: Combine margarine, garlic powder, parsley and oregano.
Stir to mix.
Pour over bread cubes; toss until coated.
Place in single layer on baking sheet.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with soup or salads.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Empty Jell-O and cheese in bowl.
Add hot water until Jell-O is dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and beat until cheese is dissolved (use beater).
Set in refrigerator until firm, but not solid.
Add pineapple, nuts, celery and cherries and fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon ice box pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate.

title: best cake recipe
directions: Mix all ingredients with fork.
Put into 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Make sugar, flour, milk, salt and baking powder into a batter.
Pour over oleo.
Pour fruit over batter and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: toffee crunch candy
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Butter foil.
Arrange crackers in single layer, salty side up.
Melt margarine and brown sugar. Boil 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers and bake 5 minutes in a 400° oven.
Take out of oven.
Immediately spread on the chocolate chips.
Let melt and smooth over all.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Break into pieces.

title: chess pie or tarts
directions: Mix, put into an uncooked shell or tart and bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or a little longer at 350°.

title: shrimp or lobster cebiche(from ecuador)
directions: Cook the shrimp in salt water together with onion and garlic. Cool and clean.
Serve in onion sauce.

title: peanut butter clay
directions: Mix all ingredients together to the desired consistency. Make any shape your imagination can come up with.

title: chinese egg rolls
directions: Cook all meats thoroughly.
Combine all ingredients, except egg roll wrappers, in a large bowl and mix well.
Place approximately one tablespoon of mixture in the center of each egg roll wrapper.
Wrap tightly and deep fry until golden brown.

title: cherry salad
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Turn into fancy bowl. Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours until chilled through.
Serves 10.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Mix and add to onion all remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer.
Pour over meat.

title: peanut butter treats
directions: Combine chips and peanut butter in large saucepan.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies. Stir until well coated.
Press mixture into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: kerry patch pie
directions: Cut together and press over bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into a ball.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: mud cups
directions: Mix pudding; add Cool Whip.
Chop up Oreos.
Using small cups, fill 1-inch with Oreo crumbs.
Mix about 1/3 of Oreo crumbs in with the pudding and Cool Whip mixture.
Spoon in pudding 1 to 2-inches high.
Sprinkle on remaining Oreo crumbs.
Add gummy worms or any other gummy bugs you can find.

title: breakfast sausage bake
directions: Spray 9x13 pan with cooking spray.
Unroll package of crescent rolls and use for crust covering bottom of pan (seal perforations).
Brown sausage and drain.
Spoon scrambled sausage over dough.
Layer potatoes over sausage.
Sprinkle cheddar cheese next.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour over other ingredients.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil until mixture forms soft in cup of cold water.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter.
Beat until smooth.
Spread into buttered 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: spinach chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine chicken, grapes, peas, spinach, celery, pasta, artichoke hearts, cucumber and green onion.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: italian meat roll
directions: Fix meat loaf like you always do.
Spread out flat about 1 inch thick; place pieces of bacon and 1/2 the cheese.
Roll up and press edges to seal.
Bake as regular meat loaf.
Right before it finishes cooking, sprinkle cheese on top and bake until melted.

title: honey crunch
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, combine cereal, oats, nuts, cinnamon and salt.
In small saucepan, combine butter, honey and brown sugar.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until butter is melted and ingredients are well blended.
Pour over cereal mixture; mix until thoroughly coated.

title: florida tropical cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended.
Put batter in 3 greased cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: fried corn
directions: Wash and cut corn off the cob in a large bowl.
Combine corn, sugar, flour, water, salt and pepper; mix well.
Melt butter over medium heat.
Add ingredients in the skillet and cook over low heat, stirring frequently, for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes, or until tender.

title: blueberry gingerbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add wet ingredients, adding tea last. Fold in berries.
Use a 9 x 13 inch prepared pan or make into muffins.
Bake at
350° until done.

title: chicken breast in casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole baking dish.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator; remove one hour before baking.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a preheated oven.

title: doggie wrap appetizer
directions: Wrap crescent dough around hot dogs and sprinkle each with cheese.
Place on cookie sheet or pan and bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes or until brown.

title: squash dressing
directions: Beat eggs, then mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: jelly cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Chill dough.
Roll out and cut to size you want.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown, about 10 minutes.
Watch carefully.
Cool slightly.
Fill with jelly and dip both sides in sugar.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Add to spinach mixture and pour into baked quiche crust or 9-inch (deep dish) pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: stuffed chicken shells
directions: Boil chicken in bouillon water.
Cook shells and drain. Prepare stuffing.
Dice chicken.
Mix all soups together with 2 1/2 cans of water.
Add about 1/2 cup of soup to stuffing to moisten.
Add diced chicken to stuffing.
Stuff shells.

title: baked cream cheese appetizer
directions: Unroll dough on lightly floured surface; press together seams to form 12 x 4-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle top of cream cheese with half of dill; lightly press dill into cream cheese.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with toasted almonds.

title: red's linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Cook the linguine according to package directions, omitting the salt. Rinse with cold water; drain and set aside.

title: swedish almond bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl with electric mixer, beat eggs for 30 seconds on medium speed.
With mixer on low, gradually add melted butter and almond extract.
Beat in sugar, flour and salt until blended, about one minute on medium speed.
Spray a jelly roll pan, 15 x 10-inches with one-inch sides with vegetable spray. Pour batter evenly into pan, smoothing out evenly to edges. Sprinkle almonds evenly over top of batter.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour, mix until smooth.
Add salt and pepper.
When mixture is smooth and bubbly, take off burner; add milk.
Put on burner.
When mixture is a little thick, add cheese. Stir continuously until thick.
Remove from burner.
Add to 2 cups cooked macaroni noodles.
Mix in 1/4 cup chopped onion; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; covered.
Remove lid. Bake for 15 minutes more.

title: german no-bake cheesecake
directions: Prepare crust in 10 x 13-inch pan.
Stir jello, water, sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
(This takes a little "elbow grease"!)
Let cool.
Whip chilled milk, then add all other ingredients to milk.
Pour into crust.
Store in freezer overnight before eating.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef, garlic, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Add other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cook over medium heat for 45 minutes.

title: chicken scallopini
directions: Pound chicken breasts very thin between 2 sheets of waxed paper (use flat side of mallet).
Dip chicken breasts first into beaten egg, then into bread crumbs.
Heat oil with clove of garlic; remove garlic.
Brown chicken for 3 minutes each side over medium heat.
Add basil and sherry.
Top with lemon slices and capers.
Simmer 5 to 6 minutes or until cooked through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Layer cookies on large round tray.
Soften cream cheese and mix with enough pineapple juice to bring to spreading consistency. Spread over cookies.
Pour can of cherry pie filling over cream cheese mixture.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix in a saucepan the cocoa, sugar and cornstarch; mix well. Cook on stove burner to medium.
Stir and cook until thick and creamy.
Serve with biscuits and butter.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Stir together mayonnaise, garlic salt, curry powder, red pepper, mustard, lemon juice and chutney.
Add chicken, celery and apple.
Cover and chill.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: layered casserole
directions: Saute beef, onion and pepper.
Drain fat and add salt.
Place potato in bottom of baking dish.
Alternate layers of carrots, rice and meat.
Pour the tomatoes all over casserole.
Cover and bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly shortening (1 1/2 cups) and eggs.
Blend in flour; shape dough into round balls, a teaspoonful at a time.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in oblong pan.
Mix tapioca and V-8 juice and pour over all.
Cover with foil and bake 3 hours at 350°.
Don't peek.

title: lemon cream cheese pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water, mixing until smooth.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until thickened and clear.
Quickly stir in egg yolks.
Bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from
heat, stir in 1/3 cup lemon juice, salt and butter.
Cool for several hours or overnight.
In a mixing bowl, blend condensed milk and cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in pudding mix and remaining lemon juice.
Fold into chilled lemon filling.
Divide and spoon into baked pie shells.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Garnish with whipped cream and lemon slices.
Yields 2 pies (12 to 16 servings).

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, soup, milk and basil/dill. Alternate layers of mixture with onion, ending with a ring of French fried onions on top. Sprinkle cheese over top and arrange 1-inch pieces bacon on top of cheese. Bake in buttered casserole dish for 30 minutes in 375° oven.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat thoroughly.
Mix dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and grated lemon rind.
Melt butter in 9-inch round cake pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over the butter or margarine.
Arrange sliced pineapple in cake pan.
Pour batter over this and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn out immediately and serve with whipped cream.

title: turkey meat loaf gravy
directions: Blend the milk into the flour until smooth.
Blend in the broth.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute; set aside.
Blend the egg substitute and evaporated skim milk in blender.
Dribble hot milk-broth-flour mixture slowly in blender, set at low speed.
Add mushrooms, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with mashed potatoes and meat loaf.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: *Put popcorn in a lightly buttered large metal mixing bowl.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Place shrimp in 2-inch pan.
Add garlic and bread crumbs then remaining ingredients.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until shrimp is firm.
Serve over rice or linguini.

title: amish friendship muffins
directions: Beat the eggs, sugar, and oil with a wire beater.
Add the dry ingredients and the milk.
Then add the pudding.
The batter will be thick; therefore, a large spoon will be better for completing the mixture.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts or raisins and 1 cup of your choice of the following: applesauce, fruit cocktail, fresh chopped apple, chopped figs, or grated carrots.
You can vary the flavorings - just vanilla, less cinnamon, almond, etc. Line muffin tins with paper liners, fill 3/4 full and bake at 400° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour only the bottoms and 1/2-inch up the sides of 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, sour cream or yogurt and bananas; mix until blended.
Stir in flour just until moistened.
Fold in nuts and pour batter into prepare pans.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove to rack to cool.
Store tightly wrapped in refrigerator.

title: easy sally lunn
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan at 350°
for 45 minutes. Serve hot with butter.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown the beef and add salt, sugar and garlic salt.
Add tomato sauce and remove from heat.
Cook noodles.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, chopped onions and green pepper.
In a buttered casserole, place a layer of noodles, a layer of cream cheese mixture and a layer of the meat mixture.
Repeat the layers until all ingredients are used.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chili quiche appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chilies and cheese in pan.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean (approximately 30 minutes). Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Cut into 1 1/4-inch squares.

title: honey angel biscuits
directions: Combine yeast and warm water.
Let set 5 minutes.
Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until crumbly.
Combine yeast mixture, buttermilk and honey.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.
Turn out on floured surface.
Knead for 1 minute. Roll out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until golden.
Makes 4 dozen 2-inch biscuits.
Serve with Honey Butter.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine rhubarb, flour and sugar and place in a greased 6 x 10-inch pan, then combine butter and shortening and cut into flour, sugar and rolled oats.
Sprinkle over rhubarb mixture. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: quick tomato sauce
directions: Saute garlic in oil in a large saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients; stir.
Heat on low until thoroughly blended.
Cook double batches and freeze unused sauce in pint or quart containers.
When needed, defrost, heat and serve.
Before serving, add cooked meatballs, hamburg or Italian sausage, if desired, or serve separately.

title: crazy beans
directions: Saute onion, celery, ground beef and pork sausage.
Add brown sugar, tomato soup and tomato paste to sauteed mixture.
Mix all ingredients together and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Place eggs in mixer; beat well.
Add coconut; beat well.
Mix flour and sugar; add to coconut-egg mixture with melted oleo.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into ungreased pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, or until firm.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Mix well and drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: shake and bake
directions: Mix well.
Dip chicken, fish or pork in milk, then into this mixture, coating it well.
Arrange in a single layer in a buttered pan.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Mix together and press into pan.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: old-fashioned cream pie
directions: Melt butter or oleo.
Add flour and milk.
Cream together with salt.
Then add brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Mix well and add coffee cream or whipping cream and milk.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°, then 45 minutes at 325°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix 1st 3 ingredients and form a ball.
Roll in pecans.
Wrap in wax paper and chill overnight.

title: dirty rice
directions: Grind or chop roast very fine.
Brown slowly in a heavy pan, adding a small amount of water as needed.
Add bell pepper, onion and garlic until tender.
Add green onions and cook for 2 minutes. Cook rice separately and add to pork mixture along with chopped parsley.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and mash artichokes with a fork.
Mix with mayonnaise and cheese.
Pour in small baking dish approximately 8 x 8-inch. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain.
Add margarine and cheese.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over macaroni and place in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until top browns.

title: skillet cookies
directions: In heavy skillet, over low heat, cook egg, sugar, oleo and dates over low heat until dates pull away from sides of skillet. Add nuts, orange slices and vanilla. Pour over rice cereal. Stir well and cool. Roll into 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar. Depending on size, this recipe makes 40 to 48 cookies.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Into a bowl, put warm water, yeast, honey and 4 cups whole-wheat flour.
Mix together and let rise twice, stirring down sponge each time (15 minutes; stir and let set 15 or more minutes). Add in the order given:
3 cups whole-wheat flour, lemon, lecithin or oil and 4 to 4 1/2 cups more whole-wheat or unbleached flour. Don't add too much flour, just enough to make a soft dough.
Knead a little.
Shape into loaves.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender.
Chill.
Onion and garlic salt may be used instead of onion and garlic.

title: cheesecake
directions: Place cream cheese into a bowl.
Stir in 1/2 cup milk until smooth.
Add remaining milk and pudding. Use mixer to mix well. Pour into graham crust and chill for 1 hour.
Garnish with desired fruit, blueberries, etc.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Return to freezer for 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: rice-vegetable-meat casserole
directions: Brown meat in butter. Crumble it as it cooks and season to taste. Place in a 2-quart casserole dish in layers, meat first, then sprinkle rice, onions, carrots, potatoes and last tomatoes. Season each layer lightly. Add enough tomato juice or water to show through. Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: In a saucepan, bring water to a boil. Whisk in gelatin and pudding mixes. Return to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and cool completely. Fold in oranges, pineapple and whipped topping. Spoon into a serving bowl. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Serves 12-14.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Combine salad oil and sugar; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Gradually add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in 2 cups finely grated carrots.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans and bake at 350° until done.

title: venison steak
directions: Soak venison in salt and vinegar water for several hours or overnight before cooking.
Rinse with cold water.
Mix flour, salt, garlic powder, hickory salt and pepper.
Dredge venison in seasoned flour.
Brown in small amount of fat in skillet over high heat.
Place in casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan; cook for 5 minutes.
Pour over venison and cover.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours, adding water as needed.

title: oatmeal caramelitas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, soda, salt and melted margarine together.
Pat 1/2 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Put chocolate chips and caramel topping, mixed with flour and nuts, on top.
Sprinkle the rest of the crust mixture on top.
Bake for 18 to 22 minutes.
(This mixture will not look done.)

title: harlequin beans
directions: Cook last 3 ingredients 20 minutes.
Add bacon and onions (fried).
Add mixed beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Make 3 wells in the dry ingredients.
Add oil, water, and vanilla.
Blend with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost, if desired.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in a large bowl.
Pour in tube pan and freeze.

title: seafood au gratin
directions: In a heavy pot, melt butter over medium heat.
Saute all seasonings until soft (about 5 minutes).
Add flour; blend well. Add hot cream.
When mixture thickens, add wine.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place crab meat and shrimp in a casserole dish; top with the sauce, which should be creamy.
Sprinkle with American cheese.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Mix cornbread mix, egg, melted margarine and corn together. Put 1/2 of mixture in a deep casserole dish.
Put sour cream a dip at a time here and there until all gone.
Put remaining mixture on top.
Cook for about 45 minutes to an hour at 400° or until done in the middle.

title: homemade salve(cures almost everything)
directions: Melt all together and strain through clean cloth.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Mix water and vinegar in pan; turn stove to low and let this warm while you mix the other ingredients.
Combine sugar, flour, egg and mustard.
Add just enough water to make mixture pasty. Now add dash of salt.
Add this mixture to water/vinegar on stove. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat when mixture starts to thicken.
Can be stored in refrigerator for about weeks.
Keep covered.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Cut fruit up in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Refrigerate.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Melt butter, add to syrup and sugar.
Mix well until all sugar is dissolved.
Add the eggs, and vanilla, and mix until smooth.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Place pecan halves on the top of the pie.
Bake at 325 degrees for 50 minutes, or until done.
You can check this with a knife.
When it comes out clean, the pie is done.
Don't forget the ice cream.

title: baked rice
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Add rice, water and salt to pan.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350°
until rice is tender.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots, covered, in small amount of water until just tender, about 15 minutes.
Add green pepper; cover and cook 3 more minutes.
Drain.

title: yum yum pot roast
directions: It is said that fire fighting is the most dangerous occupation in the United States.
Statistics put the death rate for fire fighters at 86 per 100,000 firemen.

title: fiesta squash casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Add squash and onions to boiling water; cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Set aside.
Put cheese, soup, picante sauce and seasoning in a pan on medium heat until cheese is melted.
Mash squash and onions.
Stir squash and 1 cup of chips into cheese.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with rest of chips.
Bake 30 minutes or until heated.
Makes 12 servings.

title: hot water cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, cocoa and salt together.
Blend together shortening, sugar and eggs and add 1 cup hot water and blend.
Add dry ingredients, blending well.
Then add 1 cup hot water and 1 teaspoon vanilla, mixing for 2 minutes on high.
Pour into greased, floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Top with frosting.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Place ground beef and bacon in electric skillet.
Heat to about 350°.
Cook and stir until beef is browned.
Add onion; cook until just tender.
Spoon off excess fat.
Blend flour, salt, paprika and pepper into meat.
Stir in mushroom soup.
Cook, uncovered, at about 200° for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring often. Stir in sour cream.
Heat; serve on noodles or toasted buns.

title: haystacks party mix
directions: Melt butterscotch in double boiler.
Pour over nuts and chow mein noodles which have been mixed well.
Stir until all is coated and drop by teaspoon and shape into little haystacks.
When butterscotch gets hard, the haystacks stick together tight. Refrigerate.

title: oatmeal tahini cookies
directions: Stir tahini and honey together.
Add nuts.
Add cinnamon, mixed with oats.
Stir until blended.
Drop by teaspoon on buttered or foil covered cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 or 15 minutes or until the edges are brown.

title: mincemeat drop cookies
directions: Cream butter, add sugar gradually and cream together.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy after the addition of each.
Add mincemeat. Fold in flour, baking powder and salt which have been sifted together.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet and bake in a hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes.
This makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: bean soup
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Cook all other ingredients in chicken broth for a few minutes, then add all together.
Cook until tender.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Mix together with fork.
Put small amount in little bowl and press with fork.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 9 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: health salad
directions: Combine green beans, peas and corn. Add celery, onion and pimentos.

title: miniature cheese cakes
directions: Beat cream cheese; add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs and beat until creamy.
Add vanilla and beat until blended.
Set aside.

title: yummy cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla. Stir in flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix until smooth.
Form into a small ball.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 4 to 5 hours or on high for 1 hour.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: In skillet, brown the first 5 ingredients, then add spices, seasonings and eggs.
Place in turkey.
Allow 20 minutes per pound at 300° to 325°.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Line a	8
or
9-inch pan with pastry; set aside.
In a small bowl, mix pecans and condensed milk.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Put
in
preheated 250° oven and bake for 1 1/2 hours, or until
top is browned and filling is rather firm to the touch; cool before serving.
Serves 8 persons.

title: sweet vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well with a beater. Chill and serve with vegetable platter.

title: dessert honey cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and mace; set aside.
Combine honey and orange juice; blend well. Cream together butter, vanilla, orange rind, and 1 c. sugar until smooth and well blended.
Add dry ingredients alternately with honey mixture, a little of each at a time; mix well after each addition.

title: oatmeal crunch
directions: Mix brown sugar and margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl, except potato chips.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch glass casserole.
Sprinkle the crushed potato chips on top (optional).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cook peaches sugar, cornstarch and water till thick.
Place in baking dish.
Mix Bisquick, sugar, melted butter and milk.
Drop on top of peach mix and Bake at 375 degrees for 25- 30 minutes or till golden brown.

title: chuck wagon fries
directions: Cook bacon until crisp in a 10-inch skillet.
Add potatoes and onions.
Season to taste.
Cook, covered, over low heat about 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots. If carrots are canned, they are already cooked. Drain excess liquid and cool. Cut onion and pepper and mix with carrots.
Mix cream of tomato soup with salad oil, sugar and vinegar. Add to mixture.

title: french peas
directions: Saute onion in small amount of oleo.
Barely cook peas (leave crunchy!).
Mix all ingredients, topping casserole with the French fried onions.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.
Leftovers may be frozen!

title: corn medley chowder
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion in butter, then add Spam and brown a little.
Add potato, corn, soup, milk, salt and pepper; heat to boiling.
Add chicken broth to make it a proper consistency.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp cornbread
directions: Melt oleo and saute vegetables.
Add shrimp and cook until pink.
Put cornbread into casserole and add remaining ingredients plus 1/2 can of water.
Stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.
Uncover the last 5 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with Tortilla or corn chips.

title: alaskan crab fondue
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, milk and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts. Blend in crab, bread cubes, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored. Gradually stir in crab mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry; fold in soup mixture.
Pour into
1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Makes 4 servings.

title: african slush punch
directions: Boil sugar and 6 cups
of water in a large saucepan for 3 minutes; let cool.	Mash
bananas
in blender and combine in large container with fruit
juices and 6 ounces of water.
Add sugar mixture and blend
well.
Freeze
for at least 24 hours. Remove from freezer 1
hour
before
serving.
Mash to a pulp. Add ginger ale; mix and serve.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: texas cornbread
directions: Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in salt water until tender.
Drain.
Add sour cream and chicken soup.
Melt butter and add to dressing.
Put half of the dressing in the bottom of a 9 x 14-inch casserole. Add squash and top with the rest of dressing.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: green beans caesar
directions: Mix together beans, salt, pepper, garlic, oil and vinegar. Mix until beans are well coated.
Put in baking dish.
Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Put on top of beans.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: p j's beef stew
directions: Brown stew meat over medium heat until lightly browned; add 1/2 cup water to pan.
Stir to loosen drippings.
Place browned meat in a large roasting pan and mix in all remaining ingredients. Cover and bake in oven for 3 1/2 hours at 300°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix soups and pour into rice.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: confetti rotini
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and blanche under cold running water until cool.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight allowing the flavors to meld.

title: fat city cinnamon buns
directions: Place walnuts and raisins on greased pan bottom.
Take 1 bread loaf.
Pull pieces off and scatter over walnuts and raisins.
Mix butter, milk, brown sugar and pudding.
Pour over dough in pan. Sprinkle cinnamon over the dough.
Pull apart second loaf and fill in empty spaces left from first loaf.

title: play clay recipe
directions: In saucepan, stir together baking soda and cornstarch, then add water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is consistency of moist mashed potatoes.
Turn out on a plate and cover with damp cloth until cool enough to handle.
Roll into 1/4-inch thickness.

title: guacamole
directions: Put all ingredients into blender jar. Cover. Blend on high speed approximately 30 seconds. Stop motor and stir down when necessary. Blend until creamy. Yields approximately 1 cup.

title: alaska icebox rolls
directions: Place
margarine,
sugar
and
salt in a large bowl and pour boiling
water
over and stir until well mixed.
Let set until cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water, then add yeast and egg
to margarine
mixture.
Add
flour
and
beat until well blended. Cover
and	let set in refrigerator overnight.
When ready	to use,
shape
into
rolls;
cover and let rise until doubled in size
(45 minutes to 1 hour).
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: beef bourguignonne extraordinaire
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In skillet, brown roast and place in greased 3-quart casserole.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake 3 hours.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: old fashion strawberry shortcake
directions: Blend sifted dry ingredients and shortening. Add milk. Stir only to mix and place on well floured board. Roll out 2 layers. Place together in round cake pan (greased and floured) with soft butter between layers. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Separate layers and put sweetened strawberries between and on top. Top with whipped cream. Serve hot.

title: angelic angel food cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Cool until thickened.
Fold in lemon pie filling and one (8 ounce) Cool Whip.
While Jell-O is thickening, break angel food cake into small bite-size pieces. Line a 9 x 13 pan with half of the angel food cake pieces; cover with half of lemon filling.
Spread remaining cake on top and cover with remaining filling.
Chill.
Frost with one (8 ounce) Cool Whip.
Top with shredded coconut if desired.
Makes 10 servings.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Mix all and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: seafood salad bowl
directions: In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, garlic, tarragon, mustard, capers and parsley.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour, or until ready to serve.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: In a large kettle combine sausage, potatoes, onions, carrots and chicken broth. Bring to boil, lower heat and simmer for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add sauerkraut and tomatoes. Bring to a boil and lower heat, simmer another 30 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, water and vanilla flavoring until smooth. Pour into a 2 quart glass baking dish then add drained peaches. Cook in 350 degree oven for about 1 hour or until golden brown. Allow to cool, but serve warm.

title: homemade bread
directions: Add sugar and yeast to lukewarm water.
Stir to dissolve yeast.
Add flour, salt and onion; knead until smooth.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch it down; flatten dough on oiled cookie sheet to 1-inch thick.
Oil top of dough.
Let it rise to double. Sprinkle with salt and dried rosemary.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: reception punch
directions: Mix orange juice and lemonade according to directions.
Add pineapple juice and sugar.
Mix well and store in refrigerator. Just before serving, add ginger ale, strawberries and gin or vodka.
Stir well; put in ice pineapple mold.

title: divinity fudge candy
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and water in saucepan.
Cook without stirring until syrup spins a thread 4 inches long.
Cool 2 or 3 minutes. Pour slowly into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Beat until creamy. Add nuts and flavoring.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Cut pecans into small pieces.
Mix all the ingredients in a large bowl and let it chill for about 2 hours.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening thoroughly.
Add flour, one cup at a time, with 4 eggs; alternately add 3 eggs each additional time. Add salt.
Stir in pineapple with spatula.
Pour into a greased tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar, egg yolk and vanilla until smooth. Add flour and salt. Press into the bottom of a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Frost; sprinkle with nuts (while warm). Cut into squares while warm.

title: je je's tea
directions: Mix tea bags, cloves, mint leaves and boiling water.
Add ReaLemon juice and 3 quarts water.
Strain and refrigerate mixture.
Makes 4 1/2 quarts of tea.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix Equal, Jell-O and cornstarch; then add Sprite.
Cook until thick.
Cool and add strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: crispies cookies
directions: Cream
butter,	sugar and egg.	Sift flour, soda, cream of tartar
and salt.
Add gradually until well blended.
Fold in rice cereal last.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Cover with cheese.
Mix soup and milk well.
Pour over asparagus and cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle onion rings over top (if desired) last 10 minutes of baking.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.

title: rumaki wraps
directions: You will also need toothpicks.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed and bake in 11 x 16-inch pan.
While cake is baking, mix pineapple and sugar and boil 5 minutes.

While cake is hot, punch holes in it and pour pineapple mixture over it. Let cake cool, then mix pudding as directed and pour over it. Sprinkle coconut over top, then add sliced bananas and cover all with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle generously with pecans; chill and serve. This cake is better if made and chilled overnight.

title: jeff's beef marinade
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; mix well.
Sauce is great as a marinade for London broil.
Keeps indefinitely in freezer.

title: allen's clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
The longer it sits in refrigerator, the better.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and cook in crock-pot all day.

title: mama's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light; add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add in flour, one cup at a time.
Alternate with cream, then add vanilla.
Pour in pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: strawberry sauce
directions: Cream butter, then add sugar gradually, beating well. Crush strawberries and add them a little at a time, beating after each addition until the sauce is smooth. Cover and refrigerate.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars, add vanilla and mix well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients, chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown. Makes a nice large batch.

title: kentucky chicken chowder
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion with basil and thyme in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are done. Stir often.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Break up cauliflower, broccoli and red onion.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over all.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: sugar-free oat bran muffins
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and set aside. Mix egg, applesauce and milk with whisk. Add dry ingredients using whip. You may add anything else you like. Bake in muffin pan for 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.
You can also add raisins, dates, carrots and bananas.

title: deep dark secret cake
directions: Beat brown sugar and eggs together.
Add flour, baking powder, vanilla and salt to mixture.
Fold dates and nuts in.
Bake at 350° in a cookie sheet for 30 minutes (or less).

title: infallible rice
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Combine onion, rice and hot broth.
Bring to a boil on top of range.
Cover casserole dish and place in a 325° oven for 25 minutes.
Serves 4 hungry or 6 polite people.

title: east meets west salad
directions: For salad, tear greens into bite-size pieces.
Cut stems into 1/4-inch slices.
Toast the sesame seed until brown in a small pan or skillet.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Heat milk and cheese until cheese is melted, stirring constantly.
Stir into noodle mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: In large bowl, combine beef, water, eggs, rice, 2 teaspoons of the minced onion, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly with hands and form into golf ball size balls.
Set aside.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix in order that ingredients are listed.
Chill for 1 hour or so before serving.

title: pull-apart buns
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine and mix with brown sugar and nuts. Combine cinnamon and white sugar.
Melt remaining margarine.
Dip frozen biscuits in butter and roll in sugar/cinnamon mixture. Layer in a greased Bundt pan.
Pour brown sugar mixture over top. Place in a cold oven overnight to allow to rise.
Bake in the morning at 375° for 25 minutes.
Turn Bundt pan over onto a plate while hot and serve.

title: raisin pudding
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, including soda.
Beat eggs; add to mixture, then put in milk.
Cook in double boiler for 2 hours before removing cover.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredieents in a bowl...add the hen fruit 'n milk...mix gud...slap on the griddle...whin top fills wid bubbles, flip over on t'other side.
When done, buttah 'n pore syrup on top.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco; add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Add flour and milk alternately having added baking powder to flour.
Lastly add flavoring.

title: val's squash pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over vegetables and cover with ice water.
Put a few ice cubes on top.
Set for 1 hour.
Drain.

title: fox grape wine(amish penn. dutch)
directions: Heat grapes in water (enough to almost cover) to just about boiling point.
Pour into crock containing raisins and sugar.
Add water; cover with cheesecloth and let stand in cool cellar about 3 weeks or until fermentation has ceased.
Stir twice a week. Strain and bottle but do not seal for 3 days.
Lay bottles on side.

title: hot water corn bread
directions: Mix corn
meal,
flour, sugar and salt.
Boil water for 15 minutes;
add
to mixture (should be gummy).
Use a bowl of cold water to form into corn bread ball.

title: whatits
directions: Heat oven to 250°.

Lightly grease cookie sheet with unsalted shortening. Mix nuts in flour. Beat egg whites to soft peaks; add sugar slowly beating until stiff. Fold nuts and flour into beaten egg whites. Drop mixture by teaspoons about 1 1/2-inches apart onto cookie sheet. Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove from oven and cool slightly before removing cookies to a wire rack to cool completely. Store in an airtight container.
This makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil 1 1/2 cups water.
Mix jello in water first until dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce.
Mix until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate for an hour or so to set.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix well; roll in parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: stuffed crawfish beignets
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Add garlic, seasoning and crawfish tails.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until all liquid has evaporated.
Set aside and cool completely.
Add cheeses, green onions and parsley.
Prepare biscuits.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish. Mix flour, sugar and baking powder. Add milk and mix well. Spoon batter over butter. Heat fruit with sugar and pour over dough. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruits well and add to mangoes.
Beat cream to pudding consistency, fold in mayo.
Put all ingredients together, cover, refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve with mint leaves for garnish.

title: macadamia nut chocolate mousse
directions: Mix crumbs and butter.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for
5 to 7 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: curried baked fruit(prepare the day before)
directions: Drain all fruit.
Add sugar and curry powder to melted butter. Arrange fruit and nuts in layers in casserole.
Pour butter mixture over all and bake at 325°
for 1 hour.
Refrigerate overnight; reheat at 350°
before serving.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Add celery, nuts and grapes.
Fold mayonnaise into whipped cream.
Gently fold into apple mixture.
Chill.
Serve in lettuce-lined bowl.
Makes 6 servings.

title: celery seed salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together; beat with mixer.
Bottle.
Store in refrigerator.

title: stuffed grahams
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crackers; mix well.
Spread equal amounts of peanut butter mixture on graham cracker squares. Top each cracker with another cracker square.

title: asparagus and pea casserole
directions: Arrange half of asparagus in buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Gently mix peas, cheese and soup together.
Spoon 1/2 over the asparagus.
Top with other half of pea mixture.
Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: heavenly hash(salad or dessert)
directions: Mix
all ingredients lightly.
This must be chilled for at least 24 hours.
Keeps several days.

title: crunchy apple crisp
directions: Place apples in 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Microwave 16 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Chill.

title: frijoles negros(spanish for black beans)
directions: Wash beans thoroughly then soak black beans and one green pepper in 10 cups water in large pot.
When the beans are plump, cook mixture for approximately 45 minutes or until soft.

title: chocolate cherry upside-down cake
directions: Spread pie filling in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
In another bowl, mix water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Add liquid mixture to dry mixture and stir just to moisten.
Pour batter over cherries. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in the pan.
Invert on large platter.
Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: kimball art museum's mulligatawny soup
directions: Saut onion in butter until soft.
Add carrots, green pepper, celery, rice and stock.
Simmer for about 20 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and simmer until the apple is tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
8 cups.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: low calorie thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Contains 14 calories per tablespoon.

title: molasses cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs. Add molasses. Sift the flour with cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt. Put the soda in the boiling water. Add flour mixture to the sugar mixture. Gradually add soda water, stirring constantly. Beat mixture well. The batter will be very thin, but do not add more flour. Pour into a greased and lightly floured 9 x 13 cake pan. Bake in moderate oven about 45 minutes or until when you press top of cake it leaves no dent.

title: taco casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 meat mixture, chips and cheese in 2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomato.
Serves 6.

title: pickled sweet and sour vegetables
directions: Place water in saucepan and bring to a vigorous boil.
Add vegetables to water and turn off heat.
Let vegetables stay in water 2 minutes.
Drain off water and spread vegetables out to dry.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix first five ingredients and let stand overnight.
Drain in running cold water.
Put in kettle and add next 6 ingredients. Cook over low heat 30 minutes.
Put in hot sterilized pint jars and seal.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add syrup and brown sugar.
Mix well. Add vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Lay pecan halves on top of pie. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine pumpkin, egg, oil, and sugar. Add vanilla and mix well. Add milk and soda. Mix dry ingredients and add to mixture. Fold in chips and nuts.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion and let cook some.
Then add green beans and tomato soup.
Put onto casserole dish and pile mashed potatoes on top.
Bake in oven at 350° until potatoes are brown on top.

title: *strawberries
directions: Mix jello and coconut.
Add milk, which has been tinted with the red food coloring.
Add walnuts or pecans and vanilla. Refrigerate 45 minutes.
Shape into berries and roll in red sugar. Color slivered almonds green and apply for stems.
These may be frozen or will keep in the refrigerator for several weeks.

title: coconut pies(makes two)
directions: Melt
margarine;
add sugar, eggs and vanilla flavoring. Then add
coconut,
buttermilk
and corn meal.
Mix well. Pour into pie shells and then bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans well and mix with celery and onion.
Combine sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Pour over bean mixture. Marinate overnight, stirring frequently.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken (and bone), beef and pork in covered pot with water until tender.
Let cool.
Grind in meat grinder or food processor.
Grind the potatoes and large onion; add to meat and juice.
Cook.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring often.

title: chocolate cake pudding
directions: In baking container, mix sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa.
Stir in milk, melted butter and vanilla.
Spread this mixture evenly in pan or casserole.

title: blond brownies
directions: Cream oleo and brown sugar and add egg, vanilla, flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Mix real good.
Spread in greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with butterscotch chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Layer broccoli, ham and cheese in casserole.
Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs and pour over other ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients; add black pepper and salt to taste and add 1/2 cup milk or water or until right thickness to spread in pan. Two teaspoons chili powder and small chopped onions may be added. Bake in moderate oven.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice (thick slices) sweet potatoes.
Sprinkle with sugar and nutmeg.
Add butter.
Add vanilla, salt and water.
Put in an iron skillet and cover.
Simmer over medium heat until liquid forms a syrup and potatoes are tender.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: In large mixing bowl, let ice cream and butter stand at room temperature until soft.
Beat together.
Stir in sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Blend until smooth.
Put in large plastic containers; cover and freeze.
Mixture remains spoonable.

title: savory vegetable stew
directions: Cut peppers and onions into small pieces and cook in butter until soft and onions are brown.
Add tomatoes and cook together until vegetables are tender.
Season and serve.
Makes a good sauce on rice, macaroni, spaghetti, eggs or meat.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Mix hamburger, onion soup, bread crumbs, eggs, water and ketchup together. Put in large rectangular casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from oven and spread mixed vegetables over meat, then spread mashed potatoes over vegetables. Sprinkle cheese over top and bake until cheese melts.

title: shamrock oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs. Add vanilla.
Mix in flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, M&M's and nuts.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice, onion and pepper in butter.
Add tomatoes and water.
Salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Bring to boil and simmer gently for 30 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
