Add soup mix and sour cream.
Mix in onion rings.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: valedia myers easiest best chili
directions: Melt butter; add onions and garlic.
Fry up your ground round meat with onion and garlic.
Drain off excess grease, then add your 4 Star chili.
Break it up and stir it in.
Then add your chili beans.
This may be real thick so you may need to add water for it to be thinner.
Then add your chili powder, 1 to 2 tablespoons depending on how hot you want it to be.
Cook for about 10 minutes.
Then add your Velveeta cheese.
Let it melt, stirring it in.
Serve with corn bread sticks or crush up crackers in chili and serve.

title: amaretto fudge sauce
directions: Combine cream, chocolate chips and butter in saucepan.
Heat over low heat until hot, not boiling.
Remove and stir until smooth.
Stir in vanilla and Amaretto.
Great as fondue sauce to serve with fruit or a topping for ice cream.

title: fast spaghetti
directions: Heat and saute onion, celery and green pepper in oil.
Add chopped tomatoes and spaghetti.
Add remaining ingredients and any other spices you like.
Stir well.
Cover and cook over low flame about 30 minutes.
Add water as necessary until spaghetti is al dente.
Serve with grated cheese, Italian bread and a salad.

title: pickled beets
directions: Grate beets.
Add horseradish (a little at a time), vinegar, salt and sugar to taste.
Mix well.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and beat well; mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water. Add hot water, sugar, salt, lemon juice and pineapple and place in refrigerator for 45 minutes. Take out and mix with 1 Cool Whip. Break cake in bite size pieces and add to mixture. Place in container lined with Saran Wrap and refrigerate for 24 hours. When ready to serve, turn over on plate and frost with the second Cool Whip.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Cook in little oil, celery, onion and hamburg, then add chicken and rice soup, mushroom soup, water, soy sauce and rice. Cook in greased casserole 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Add cherry pie filling, pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and coconut. Refrigerate and serve.

title: rye bread with dill dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Cut out center of round rye bread and fill with dip.
Cut the center portion in pieces and serve with dip.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Melt butter in oven in baking dish.
Mix cheese, flour, salt and pepper.
Cut potatoes in wedges and coat with cheese mixture. Put in dish with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn over after first 30 minutes.

title: shannon's chocolate eclair
directions: Make pudding in large bowl according to the directions on the box.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer graham crackers to cover bottom of pan, then a layer of pudding, layer of graham crackers, layer of pudding and layer of graham crackers.

title: big mama's sweet potato pudding
directions: Place in 1-quart casserole.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm, plain or whipped cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat until light and fluffy the sugar, shortening and eggs. Add vanilla.
Mix thoroughly the buttermilk and soda, then add alternately with flour to mixture. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: linda's cranberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop berries in blender.
In small bowl combine berries, oats, sugar and orange extract.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and allspice.
Combine eggs, milk and oil; add to dry mixture, then add cranberry mixture.
Stir until moist.
Pour into 2 (9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 3-inch) bread pans.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes, then remove from pans.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Combine water, butter, soda and raisins in a large bowl and let stand about 1 hour.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Season with salt and pepper.
In a large frying pan, heat olive oil.
Add chicken and cook turning after 5 minutes or until lightly browned on both sides.
Add onion to pan and cook for a couple of minutes or until softened.
Add garlic and cook for about 30 seconds.
Add wine, tomatoes and oregano.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Season with additional salt and pepper; sprinkle with parsley and serve with your favorite pasta.

title: turkey noodle casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Saute pepper, celery and onion until tender. Fold in turkey, noodles, pimento, mushroom soup and milk.
Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan and Cheddar.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Mix salt, cabbage and carrot.
Let stand 1 1/2 hours.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix last four ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Chill for 2 hours or overnight.

title: taco pie
directions: Add taco seasoning, water and sliced olives to cooked meat. Simmer for 3 minutes.
Separate dough; press into ungreased pie pan to form crust.
Sprinkle 1 cup crushed corn chips on crust. Spoon on seasoned meat.
Spread on sour cream.
Add cheese and remaining chips.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: funnel cake
directions: You will need a 1 funnel.

title: carrot cake muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased muffin tins. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes. Yield: 12 muffins.

title: no-name salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and put in refrigerator. Crumble cookies and stir in a couple of hours before eating. Double everything except cookies for a large batch.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Lay graham crackers on well-greased 11 x 15-inch cookie sheet. Boil the margarine and sugar 2 minutes only.
Add nuts and pour over crackers.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.
Break into serving size.

title: cameo cake(from southern living)
directions: *Omit white chocolate for moist yellow cake.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350°.

title: tasty spread for hamburgers or steak
directions: Cream together, butter, Blue cheese and mustard.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour to let the flavors mingle.
Spread on cooked steak, hamburgers or hamburger buns.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients together for five minutes, then remove spices.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Work shortening and sugar well into the flour.
Add yeast
mix
and
milk; mix well.
Put out on dough board and work
well.
Roll
out;
cut
with large biscuit cutter.
Brush with butter.
Fold in half.
Put in pan. Brush butter on top.
Put damp towel over them.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Set out.
Let
rise.
Bake
at 400° about 15 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together sugar and shortening. Add egg and beat well.
Add flour, milk and vanilla; mixing after each addition.
Roll out dough on lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness. Cut with a floured cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet in oven for 15 minutes.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Preheat the blender.
Put the butter on medium heat. Beat the yolks.
When the butter just starts to sizzle, pour it slowly into the beaten yolks (while beating) through the barely open top of the blender.
Add lemon juice.
Add salt and white pepper to taste.

title: asparagus with pimentos
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, cook asparagus in boiling salted water until tender, about 8 minutes. Meanwhile, in a skillet, brown bread crumbs in butter. Drain asparagus; place in a serving dish. Sprinkle with crumbs, cheese and pimentos.

title: cooked dressing for fruit salad
directions: Combine sugar, mustard,
salt
and
vinegar and heat to boiling.
Pour over
well beaten egg yolks, stirring constantly. Cook until	thickened,
beating
with
rotary egg beater. Add butter.
Just
before
serving,
add
1/2 cup heavy cream, whipped, or thin cream or milk.
Do not dilute vinegar.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: realemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In heavy saucepan, combine 1 1/3 cups sugar and cornstarch.
Add ReaLemon.
In small bowl, beat egg yolks.
Add to ReaLemon mixture.
Gradually add water, stirring constantly.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until mixture boils and thickens, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine.
Stir until melted.
Pour into baked pie shell.
In small mixer bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Gradually add remaining 1/3 cup sugar.
Beat until stiff, but not dry.
Spread on pie; seal edges.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Cool.
Chill before serving.

title: banana pineapple cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Beat eggs; add bananas, oil, undrained pineapple and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients.
Fold together; do not beat.
Pour into a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Remove and cool on rack.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Saute onions and paprika in shortening slowly for 10 minutes. Add disjointed chicken.
Cover pan and simmer until golden brown. Add broth; cook until tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add water, if needed.
Blend flour, seasonings and sour cream 5 minutes before chicken is done.
Stir into mixture slowly.
Serve with noodles or dumplings.

title: potato cheese casserole(12 servings)
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients thoroughly; divide in half (to be layered later) and set aside.
Gently blend the cheeses together; divide in half (to be layered later) and set aside. Divide hash browns in half now (to be layered later).
Mix together cornflakes and margarine thoroughly.
Layer 1/2 the hash browns into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour 1/2 the milk and soup mixture evenly over first layer; follow with 1/2 the cheese blend, then repeat:
potatoes, soup and cheese.
Sprinkle cornflake mixture
evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: angel's "miracle" whip cake
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburg; drain and cool.
Combine additional items and serve.

title: beef standing rib roast
directions: Have the retailer remove the backbone (for easier carving) and tie roast.
Season meat with salt and pepper.
Place roast, fat side up, on rack in open roasting pan.
Insert roast meat thermometer so bulb is centered in the thickest part, making sure bulb does not rest in fat or on bone.
Do not add water.
Do not cover.

title: holiday breakfast
directions: Mix milk, salt, mustard and eggs and pour over other ingredients tossing lightly.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate 12 hours.
Bake 35 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: shrimp or crabmeat dip
directions: Melt butter. Sauce onions and parsley. Blend in flour, whipping cream and cheese. Stir until cheese is melted. Fold in crabmeat (if too thin, add a little flour). Serve hot with crackers.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Cool and crumble half in bottom of punch bowl.
Add 1 box of pudding mixed with 3 cups of milk as directed on box.
(Mix one box at a time or it may get too thick.) Add pudding to cake crumbs; then add 1/2 can of fruit cocktail with juice and 1/2 can of cherries (mainly around the edges, so it will show).
Add 1/2 of the 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts, if desired.
Repeat all layers.
Leave enough cherries to put on top of Cool Whip.

title: lasagne(use sauce recipe by helen seitz)
directions: In large bowl, mix 3 eggs, beaten, into 36 ounces Ricotta cheese and refrigerate until ready to assemble.
About 1 hour before assembling, cook lasagne noodles; drain and cool in cold water.
Dry on paper towels.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter, oil and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend well after each.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Pour into greased, floured 10-inch tube pan.
Start in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes.

title: irish spaghetti
directions: In frying pan, brown ground beef, diced onion and chopped green peppers.
In medium saucepan, heat soup with milk.
Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Preparation time:
25 minutes.

title: jim's favorite texas hot cocoa cake
directions: Melt shortening with oleo, cocoa and water in pan.
Bring to a boil and stir.
Sift sugar and flour in large bowl.
Pour liquid mixture over flour mixture and beat until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
It's best to use a jelly roll pan.
When you take the cake out of the oven, having icing ready to pour on the hot cake.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients together.
Stir up.
Melt butter and mix with corn flakes.
Sprinkle over top.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: rumaki
directions: You will also need toothpicks.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Melt margarine, then add the cheese.
Mix well.
Then add the rest of the ingredients, Rice Krispies last.
Roll into small balls and flatten.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: santa fe chicken
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Heat oil and fry chicken for 2 minutes.
Add onion, pepper and garlic; cook until tender, about 4 minutes.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Add broth to equal 1 cup.
Add chicken broth to tomato liquid to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add liquid to skillet; bring to boil.
Stir in rice and reserved tomatoes. Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand until liquid is absorbed. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: applesauce meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients, except catsup, barbecue sauce and water. Make into small balls and brown in hot fat.
Remove meatballs from pan to baking dish.
In small bowl, combine the catsup, barbecue sauce and water.
Pour mixture over meatballs.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Delicious served over rice.

title: old settlers' baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon, and onions.
Add and mix other ingredients.
Bake in a casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: divinity
directions: Place sugar, corn syrup and water in heavy saucepan.
Over medium heat, cook to hard ball stage (248°).
Remove from heat and let stand until temperature drops to 220°, without stirring.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix the beans and onion in a 3-quart casserole.
Combine other ingredients and mix with beans.
Place bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Place in casserole.
Combine soup, eggs, cheese, onion and mayonnaise.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Add salt, soda and flour; blend.
Add nuts.
Shape into rolls and freeze until ready to bake.
Make each roll about as big around as a half dollar. Slice thin to bake.

title: rhubarb crumb cake
directions: Mix topping ingredients together and set aside.

title: mrs. curran's baltimore crab soup
directions: In an 8-quart soup pot, combine and simmer for 2 to 3 hours barley, lima beans, cabbage, tomatoes, onions, celery and water. After simmering 2 to 3 hours, add carrots, 1/2 dozen live crabs and seasoning.
Return soup to a boil and simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Chop bacon, cook and drain (reserving 2 tablespoons grease); simmer about 30 to 60 minutes.
In small frypan, make a roux with the 2 tablespoons of bacon grease and 5 or 6 tablespoons flour.
After roux or paste has cooked 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly over medium-low heat, begin to add liquid from the soup to form a gravy liquid, then add to soup pot.
Stir and cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Let the soup stand for at least 30 minutes (60 is better).
Taste and adjust seasonings, Old Bay and salt.
Soup is served with a 1/2 crab in each bowl with crusty bread.
(I like pumpernickel.)

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, baking powder and salt thoroughly and add jalapeno peppers, bell pepper and onions.
Mix peppers in meal to separate and distribute evenly in mixture, then stir in peppers and onions.
Add corn, sour cream, eggs and cooking oil; stir until smooth.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine the sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add the milk.
Cook in a deep skillet, stirring constantly, until thickened.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon and onions.
Cook until onions are soft.
Put in large pot.
Add potatoes and clam juice.
Cook until potatoes are soft.
(If juice doesn't cover potatoes, add some water.)
When potatoes are cooked, add milk, clams and salt and pepper to taste. Cook until hot (do not boil).
If a thicker chowder is wanted, make paste of melted butter and flour.
Add to chowder.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix and beat Bisquick, milk and cheeses for 30 seconds.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 11 minutes at 450°.
Mix butter, garlic powder and parsley together and brush over top of biscuits.

title: peanut haystacks
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Butter an 8-inch spring-form pan.
In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate with vanilla and coffee (and brandy).
Add butter, sugar and almonds; heat mixture until butter melts.
Remove pan from the heat.
Beat egg yolks and stir into chocolate mixture.
Whip egg whites just until stiff and fold into chocolate mixture.
Turn batter into pan and bake in the middle of the oven for 45 minutes.
The cake will have some cracks in the top and a tester won't come out clean.
Cool completely on a rack and remove the side of the pan.

title: chocolate french toast
directions: Crack the eggs into a mixing bowl.
Beat until well mixed.
Add chocolate flavored milk.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour egg mixture into a pie plate.
Put half of the butter in a skillet.
Put it on a burner.
Turn the burner to medium-high heat.
Dip one slice of bread into egg mixture.
Turn bread over to coat the other side. Put on skillet.
Repeat with another slice of bread.
Cook until bottoms are brown.
To see, lift bread with turner to see underneath.
Remove bread with turner.
Put leftover butter in skillet.
Repeat steps 3 and 4. Turn off burner.
Remove the skillet.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Top with filling or syrup which is optional.
Serves two people.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Pound
salt,
pepper
and
flour
into cutlet; brown in butter.
Add
remaining ingredients.
Simmer for about 1 hour, all liquid
should be gone or just a small amount left to pour over rice if wanted.
Can also use chicken or turkey.

title: butterscotch surprise
directions: Melt margarine and mix with flour and pecans.
Spread on bottom of pan or dish.
Bake until brown and chill.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and boil for 6 minutes.
Mix marshmallow cream and peanut butter and vanilla.
Whip with spoon. Pour in buttered pan.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Heat sugar, vinegar, mustard seed, celery seed and salt.
Pour over cabbage, onions and peppers.
Mix well and let stand.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 8 x 12-inch dish. Mix milk, flour, baking powder and sugar.
Add to melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Spread sliced peaches on top (do not stir).
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: pinwheel cookies
directions: Make dough; roll thin.
Spread on sausage (which is at room temperature).
Roll up like a jelly roll and chill.
Slice thin and bake in moderate oven at 350° until cookies are light brown.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Cook together into fine thick sauce.
Cool.
Then add 1 cup finely chopped Velveeta cheese and 5 or 6 finely cut marshmallows (or just some miniature marshmallows).
Add 1 cup pineapple.
Add nuts to suit your taste.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, soup, rice and cooked onion. Stir in sour cream. Grease a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish and put all of the ingredients into dish. Cook in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over the casserole and bake for 15 more minutes.

title: tangy mustard cauliflower
directions: Place cauliflower in casserole dish.
Add water and cover with lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 8 to 9 minutes or until tender-crisp.

title: billie's bread pudding
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg together. Mix remaining ingredients together.
Lightly butter 2 quart baking dish.
Add egg and sugar mixture.
Add milk mixture slowly stirring lightly.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Set in deep pan hot water and bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Knife inserted in center should come out clean.
Delicious.
Custardy.
Serves 6.

title: coleslaw salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in mayonnaise, 1/2 cup cold water, vinegar and salt.
Chill until partially set. Beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in vegetables.
Pour into 4 cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Serves 8.

title: quick apple crisp
directions: Place apple slices in bowl.
Combine other ingredients. Sprinkle on apple.
Cook on High 4 to 5 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute.
Serves 1.

title: zucchini marmalade
directions: Boil the sugar and zucchini for 5 minutes.
Add crushed pineapple and cook 1 minute.
Turn off heat and add 1 large package orange jello or any flavor.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into jars and seal. Keep in refrigerator.

title: dad's cheese spread
directions: Chop cheese in blender or food processor.
Mix with rest of ingredients.

title: pear cake(club member: lee higginbotham)
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Pour into greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes (check at 1 hour).

title: new orleans fruit cake
directions: Combine mixed fruits, red cherries, pecans and green cherries in large bowl.
Sift sugar, flour, salt and baking powder together into bowl over fruit mixture, coating fruit well.
Grease large loaf pan; line with double layers of waxed paper.
Spoon batter into pan; press down firmly.
Bake at 300°
for 2 hours.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Sauerkraut is shredded cabbage that has been pickled.
I use a large bag or can of prepared sauerkraut, add a large onion (cut up) and about 3 tablespoons of bacon drippings for flavor.
Cook together with a roast pork for best flavoring, until onion is tender.

title: audrey's salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in an oblong glass dish. Refrigerate.
Serve each portion on a bed of lettuce.

title: taco chip dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add beans, tomato sauce and seasoning mix until warmed through.
Spread this in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with sour cream.
Sprinkle sour cream with chili powder as desired.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese and heat in oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: veal scallopini(mock)
directions: Amounts of ingredients vary to number of servings.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Season ground beef with salt and pepper; saute and drain.
In a 3-quart casserole, mix together the squash, ground beef, macaroni, canned sauce, cheese and garlic powder.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese lightly over top.
Bake in a 350° oven, covered, for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 10 more minutes, until cheese is lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: carrot salad
directions: Boil whole carrots; let cool and slice.
Don't overcook.

title: lime pickles
directions: Mix water and lime; add cucumbers.
Stir often.
Soak 24 hours. Wash well.
Soak in clear water 3 hours.
Drain well and add other ingredients.
Let stand overnight.
Heat and boil 35 minutes.
Can and seal.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil 6 cups of water and then add the broccoli, onion, garlic powder, margarine and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Cube cheese and add to this mixture along with the milk.
Make a mixture of the flour and 1/2 cup of water and add to the soup.
Stir constantly until thickened.

title: beef picadillo dip
directions: Brown beef in heavy skillet.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Serve hot with corn chips or tostados.

title: chex party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250 degrees.
Melt margarine, stir in Worcestershire sauce, garlic and salt.
Pour over mixed cereal and nuts, mix well.
Bake on cookie sheet for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool on paper towels.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Melt margarine and brown sugar in a saucepan.
Add coconut, pecans and cornflakes.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13 freezable container.
Spread ice cream over mixture and top with the remaining mixture.
Put in freezer until ready to serve. Drizzle with chocolate syrup and top with Cool Whip and cherries.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice the cucumbers.
Mix the salt with the peppers and onions and cover with crushed ice.
Let stand in refrigerator for 3 hours.
Drain and add sugar, turmeric, vinegar, cloves and mustard seed.
Mix; drain vegetables.
Put on low heat and heat to scalding point but don't boil.
Seal in hot jars (using the instructions for a reliable canning manual).
Makes about 5 quarts.

title: cowboy potatoes
directions: Fry bacon; set aside.
In bacon grease fry potatoes, onions and bell peppers until tender.
Dice bacon; add to potato mixture. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: empanadas
directions: Cut shortening into flour. Add milk to vinegar. Add liquids and salt to flour mixture. Blend dough.

title: microwave fruit compote
directions: Drain fruit and combine in baking dish.
Make sauce by combining 1/2 cup pineapple syrup, 1/2 cup apricot syrup, 1/2 cup syrup from peaches along with brown sugar and butter.
Microwave for 5 to 6 minutes on High, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Mix cornstarch with 1/2 cup liquid from drained fruit and add to fruit to thicken.
Add cinnamon and flavoring and pour over fruit and microwave for 10 to 15 minutes on High.
Serves 6.

title: easy santa cookies
directions: Spread red icing over top 1/3 of cookie.
Press 1 mini marshmallow below the edge corner of the icing to make a santa hat.
Sprinkle and press coconut flakes beside marshmallow to complete santa hat.
Press two chocolate chips for the eyes, and a red hot for the nose.
Sprinkle and press coconut flakes on the bottom 1/4 of the cookie for Santa's beard.
Serve and enjoy!

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Brown spareribs in oven at 350°.
Pour off accumulated fat when almost done.
Add sauce; rest of ingredients mixed together. Bake until tender.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together.
Form into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place in baking dish.
Pour 1 can of tomato soup over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot wassail for christmas
directions: Cut the orange into a cube and slice.
Stick cloves decoratively into slices.
Blend juices together, add peppermints (optional pineapple and cinnamon), float orange slices on top, and bring all to a boil until the peppermints melt.
Reduce heat. Keep warm until serving.

title: golobki (stuffed cabbage)
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water until tender all through.
Drain and cool.
Take leaves apart, separate and dry on cloth.
Mix ground beef, rice, diced onions, salt, pepper and catsup.
Place mixture in cabbage leaf.
Be generous but don't overstuff.
Fold over once, fold left and right edges in.
Fold over.
Press lightly to squeeze out any juices.

title: lena's pork and beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp; set aside to drain.
Mix mustard, ketchup and brown sugar with onion and pepper.
Add to beans and stir lightly. Do not drain liquid off beans.
Add crumbled bacon on top of mixture and bake 10 to 15 minutes or until it bubbles, around 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except apples and flavoring and mix well. Add apples and flavoring and blend. Grease and flour pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°. Let cool in pan.

title: enchiladas soup
directions: Saute onion and chicken and add all other ingredients and simmer 45 minutes.
(Thicken with 2 tablespoons cornstarch in 1 cup cold water; pour into mixture.)
Bake your own corn tortilla strips or buy as chips and crush into bowls; add soup and top with any or all of the following:
shredded cheese, chopped cilantro, diced tomatoes or diced onions.
Enjoy and expect lots of compliments!

title: pancakes(makes about 10)
directions: Mix dry ingredients in one bowl.
Beat eggs in another bowl; stir in nonfat milk and melted margarine.
Combine wet and dry ingredients.
Stir just until dry ingredients are wet.
Use about 3 tablespoons of mixture for each pancake.
Cook over low heat until bubbles appear on top.
Turn and brown on other side.

title: homemade chili
directions: In a large saucepan, cook ground beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is brown; drain.
Stir in everything else. Bring to boiling; reduce heat and cover.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: tahoe brunch
directions: Butter the bread with 1/2 cup butter.
Brown mushrooms and onion until tender in 3 tablespoons butter.
Brown sausage and drain.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole. Layer 6 slices of bread, 1/2 mushroom mixture, 1/2 sausage and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers. In a mixing bowl beat together eggs, milk, mustards, nutmeg and pepper.
Pour over casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Sprinkle parsley on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Can be prepared up to 24 hours in advance.)

title: spicy salisbury cutlets with sweet onion relish
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the ground beef, red and green peppers, bread crumbs, Dijon mustard, chili powder, hot pepper flakes, onion powder, garlic powder, paprika, black pepper, dried basil, thyme and egg. Mix well. Shape the mixture into 4 patties. In a skillet, heat 1 Tbsp. of the oil. Saute Salisbury steaks, about 5 minutes on each side, until golden brown. Remove from pan and keep warm in oven. In the skillet, heat the remaining 1 Tbsp. oil. Saute the red onions for 3 minutes. Add the apple juice and honey. Saute until onions are golden brown. Serve relish over Salisbury steaks.

title: fake lasagna
directions: Bring hamburger and onion.
Drain off grease.
Cook spirals according to package directions and drain off water when done. Return to pan and add onion and hamburger mixture.
(Be sure everything is drained well.)
Add spaghetti sauce and mix well. Cover the bottom of a casserole dish with this mixture.
Then cover with a layer of cheese.
Make a second layer of meat sauce and top with remaining cheese.
Cook at 350° until cheese is lightly brown and sauce bubbles.

title: parmesan bread sticks
directions: Cut crust from bread.
Cut each piece into 4 pieces.
Mix together the margarine and garlic salt.
Dip each slice of bread into margarine mixture and roll in cheese.
Place on a baking sheet and bake in a 425°
oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: rice pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar together until creamy.
Add eggs. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 9X13 greased pan or baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add flour and spices gradually.
Add milk and vanilla.
Chill dough a few minutes. Roll out 1/2-inch thick on floured board.
Cut out and bake.

title: fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter.
Add vanilla.
Sift cocoa and powdered sugar together and add to cheese mixture.
Mix and add nuts and pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Allow to cool before cutting.

title: double-baked potatoes with ham, cheese and mushrooms
directions: Microwave potatoes for 20 to 25 minutes on High power.

title: quick strawberry pie(very low calorie)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and stir until dissolved. Pour into a baked 9-inch pie shell.
Put in refrigerator and when it sets, spread lite Cool Whip on top.
Mixture will jell quickly.

title: cranberry salad
directions: When jello is partly thickened, add remaining ingredients.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown ground beeef;
drain.
Mix with other ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: crab-broccoli dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and chill overnight.
Hollow round Hawaiian bread and fill just before serving.
Serve with crackers and leftover chunks of bread.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine & sugar well. Roll into balls. Let set on waxed paper until chocolate mixture is ready. Melt chocolate and wax over hot water. Dip balls one at a time and place on waxed paper.

title: tropical chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill. Serve on a plate of lettuce.

title: praline cookies
directions: Lay crackers side by side on cookie sheet to fill.
Boil butter and sugar 2 minutes while stirring.
Add pecans and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool and cut or break into pieces.

title: garlic lover's guacamole
directions: Peel and pit avocado.
Peel and coarsely chop garlic.
Place avocado and garlic in food processor or blender and puree until smooth.
Transfer to serving dish and blend in salsa, sour cream and lime juice.
Serve with chips, vegetables or chunks of sourdough bread.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onions.
Drain fat; stir in Mexe beans, tomato sauce, green chilies and taco seasoning.
Layer 1/2 the tortillas on bottom of an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Spread 1/2 the mixture of meat over and sprinkle with 1/2 the cheese.
Repeat 1/2 the layers.
Bake 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
